{"title_page": "Paris Berelc", "text_new": "{{Short description|American actress and model}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use American English|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Paris Beelc\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = <!-- not used if same as stage name -->\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1998|12|29}}\n| birth_place        = [[Milwaukee, Wisconsin]], U.S.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://younghollywood.com/scene/things-you-should-know-about-the-actresses-behind-netflix-s-alexa-katie.html/amp|title=Things You Should Know About The Actresses Behind Netflix's \"Alexa & Katie\"!|date=April 17, 2018|work=[[Young Hollywood]]|access-date=December 16, 2019}}</ref>\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nationality        = <!-- not used if same as birth location -->\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Actress\n* model\n}}\n| years active       = 2012\u2013present\n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Paris Berelc''' (born December 29, 1998<ref>{{cite tweet|last=Berelc|first=Paris|user=parisberelc|number=681200414931292160 |title=Thank you for the early birthday wishes! But my birthday is the 29th not the 28th xo \ud83d\ude18 |date=December 27, 2015 |access-date=June 4, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.twistmagazine.com/posts/see-stylish-celeb-polaroids-from-paris-berelc-s-sweet-16-party-48662/photos/paris-berelc-birthday-polaroids-1-71682 | title=See Stylish Celeb Polaroids from Paris Berelc's Sweet 16 Party | work=[[Twist (magazine)|Twist magazine]] | date=December 30, 2014 | accessdate=December 29, 2015}}</ref>) is an American actress and model. She is known for her roles as Skylar Storm in the [[Disney XD]] series ''[[Mighty Med]]'' and ''[[Lab Rats: Elite Force]]'', and Alexa Mendoza in the [[Netflix]] sitcom ''[[Alexa & Katie]].''\n\n== Career ==\nBerelc is of half [[Filipinos|Filipino descent]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/03/alexa-katie-season-2-ending-netflix-heather-wordham-1201943530/|title='Alexa & Katie' Boss Discusses How That Kooky Ending Was Believable and Season 2 Possibilities|first1=Hanh|last1=Nguyen|first2=Hanh|last2=Nguyen|date=March 26, 2018}}</ref> She was discovered by [[Ford Models]] at the age of nine, and was featured in ads from [[Kohl's]], Boston Store, [[Sears]], and [[K-mart]]. She appeared on the cover of [[American Girl]] magazine for their November/December Issue in 2009. In 2010, at the age of twelve, Berelc took her first acting classes at the Acting Studio Chicago. Two years after, Berelc's parents decided to take her to [[Los Angeles]] to try acting professionally. She began her professional acting career in 2013, at the age of fourteen.<ref name=\"Sweety High Blog\">{{cite web|url=https://blog.sweetyhigh.com/blog/celebrity-news/paris-berelc-mighty-med|title=Paris Berelc Chats Mighty Med and Super Powers!|author=Veronica|website=Sweety High Blog|date=April 14, 2014}}</ref>\n\nBeginning in 2013, Berelc starred as Skylar Storm on the [[Disney XD]] action sitcom ''[[Mighty Med]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|last = Ng|first = Philiana|url = http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/disney-xd-sets-debut-mighty-623331|title = Disney XD Sets Debut for 'Mighty Med' Comedy Series (Exclusive)|date = September 9, 2013|work = [[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date = September 12, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneyxdmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=3156446&type=Main |work=Disney XD Medianet |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Fpr5Jvts |url-status=dead |archivedate=April 12, 2013 |title=Mighty Med |year=2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneyxdmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=3156446&type=lead |title=Paris Berelc Lands Lead Role |work=Disney XD Medianet |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130813074138/http://www.disneyxdmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=3156446&type=lead |archivedate=August 13, 2013}}</ref> In 2015, Berelc portrayed Molly in the [[Disney Channel Original Movie]], ''[[Invisible Sister]]'', which premiered in October.<ref name=InvisibleSister>{{cite news |last=Bibel|first=Sara |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/01/09/disney-channel-greenlights-original-movies-invisible-sister-starring-rowan-blanchard-paris-berelc-further-adventures-in-babysitting-starring-sabrina-carpenter-sofia-carson/348327/ |title=Disney Channel Greenlights Original Movies 'Invisible Sister' Starring Rowan Blanchard & Paris Berelc & 'Further Adventures in Babysitting' Starring Sabrina Carpenter & Sofia Carson |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=January 9, 2015 |accessdate=January 10, 2015}}</ref> The same year, ''Mighty Med'' ended its run, but Berelc continued to play Skylar Storm on its [[Spin-off (media)|spinoff]] series ''[[Lab Rats: Elite Force]]'', which premiered on March 2, 2016.<ref>{{cite journal |first=Elizabeth|last=Wagmeister |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/disney-xd-lab-rats-elite-force-spinoff-mighty-med-1201585323/ |title=Disney XD Greenlights 'Lab Rats' and 'Mighty Med' Spinoff Series |journal=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=September 3, 2015 |accessdate=September 4, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/09/lab-rats-mighty-med-end-spinoff-series-disney-xd-1201513610/|title=Lab Rats & Mighty Med Spin-off Series to Succeed the Two Comedies on Disney XD|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=September 3, 2015|accessdate=September 3, 2015}}</ref> \n\nIn April 2017, Berelc was cast in the co-lead role of Alexa in ''[[Alexa & Katie]]'', a [[multi-camera]] [[Netflix]] sitcom, which premiered March 23, 2018.<ref name=\"DH-A&K\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/04/alexa-katie-netflix-high-school-multi-camera-comedy-series-1202064823/|title=Netflix Orders High-School Multi-Camera Comedy Series 'Alexa & Katie'|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=April 7, 2016|access-date=April 7, 2017}}</ref> In 2019, she starred in the [[Netflix original film]] ''[[Tall Girl]]'' as Liz.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/netflix-casts-ava-michelle-tall-girl-1178756|title=Netflix Finds Its 'Tall Girl'|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2020-01-10}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Television and film roles\n|-\n! Year\n! Show\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2013\u20132015\n| ''[[Mighty Med]]''\n| Skylar Storm\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Just Kidding (TV series)|Just Kidding]]''\n| Herself\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Invisible Sister]]''\n| Molly\n| [[Disney Channel Original Movie]]\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Lab Rats: Elite Force]]''\n| Skylar Storm\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''WTH: Welcome to Howler''\n| Sofia\n| Web series; recurring role, 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''#SquadGoals''\n| Brittany Gomez\n| Film, a.k.a. ''Deadly Scholars''\n|-\n| 2018\u2013present\n| ''[[Alexa & Katie]]''\n| Alexa\n| Lead role<ref name=\"DH-A&K\" />\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[The Thundermans]]''\n| Phoebe Actor\n|Episode: \"The Thundredth\"\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Sugar Rush (2018 TV series)|Sugar Rush]]''\n| Herself\n| Guest judge; episode: \"Science of Sweets\" \n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Confessional''\n| June\n| Film\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Tall Girl]]''\n| Liz\n| Film<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/netflix-casts-ava-michelle-tall-girl-1178756|website=The Hollywood Reporter|date=January 24, 2019|title=Netflix Finds Its 'Tall Girl'|access-date=January 29, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{TableTBA}}\n| ''[[Hubie Halloween]]''\n| {{TableTBA}}\n| ''Upcoming direct-to-video film''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/adam-sandler-kevin-james-julie-bowen-maya-rudolph-netflix-comedy-1202650376/|title=Adam Sandler Sets Next Netflix Comedy With All-Star Cast Including Kevin James, Julie Bowen, Maya Rudolph & Many More|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=July 2