vember 23, 2018|work=Boston Globe|date=November 14, 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Democratic primary==\n===Candidates===\n====Potential====\n*[[Jeff Bussgang]], venture capitalist and lecturer at [[Harvard Business School]]<ref name=\"bostonglobe\"></ref>\n*[[Mo Cowan]], former U.S. Senator<ref name=\"bostonglobe\"></ref>\n*[[Benjamin Downing]], former State Senator<ref name=\"bostonglobe\"></ref>\n*[[Maura Healey]], incumbent [[Massachusetts Attorney General]]<ref name=\"bostonglobe\"></ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lowellsun.com/opinion/ci_32282765/whos-ed-markeys-rearview-mirror-maura-healey|title=Who's in Ed Markey's rearview mirror? Maura Healey|work=Lowell Sun|last=Locas|first=Peter|date=November 20, 2018|accessdate=November 26, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Joe Kennedy III]], Current U.S. Senate Candidate and U.S. Representative for [[Massachusetts's 4th congressional district]]<ref name=\"bostonglobe\"></ref>\n*[[Eric Lesser]], State Senator and Former White House Aid under President Obama <ref name=\"bostonglobe\"></ref>\n*[[Seth Moulton]], U.S. Representative for [[Massachusetts's 6th congressional district]] and former candidate for President in [[2020 United States presidential election|2020]]<ref name=\"bostonglobe\"></ref>\n*Robert Rivers, chairman and chief executive of [[Eastern Bank]]<ref name=\"bostonglobe\"></ref>\n*[[Marty Walsh (politician)|Marty Walsh]], Mayor of Boston<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.metro.us/news/local-news/boston/consultant-sees-walsh-possible-2022-gov|title=\nConsultant sees Walsh as possible 2022 gov contender|work=Metro|last=Service|first=Statehouse News|date=April 30, 2018|accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://newbostonpost.com/around-new-england/peter-lucas-weight-throwing-marty-walsh-is-the-mayor-of-massachusetts/|title=\nWeight-Throwing Marty Walsh Is the \u2018Mayor of Massachusetts\u2019|work=NewBostonPost|last=Locus|first=Peter|date=June 19, 2018|accessdate=November 26, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite 