stonglobe.com/metro/2018/11/13/you-hate-read-this-story-that-speculates-about-who-might-run-for-massachusetts-governor/qjfmPxjJk3qZeQLdxXGybP/story.html|accessdate=November 23, 2018|work=Boston Globe|date=November 14, 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n====Candidates who have Expressed Interest in the Past====\n*[[Setti Warren]], Former Mayor of Newton and 2018 Gubernatorial Candidate <ref>{{cite news|last=Prim|first=Alexandra|title=Setti Warren announces bid for gov. in Mass|date=May 20, 2017|url=http://www.nbcboston.com/news/local/Setti-Warren-Announces-Bid-for-Gov-in-Mass-423355704.html}}</ref>\n*[[Evan Falchuk]], Former Gubernatorial Candidate<ref name=\"The Boston Globe\">{{cite news|last1=Ramos|first1=Nestor|title=Evan Falchuk, former independent candidate, switches to Democratic Party|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2017/02/12/switch/b84oZEjZyFyGSnn5OHl5jO/story.html|accessdate=15 February 2017|publisher=The Boston Globe|date=12 February 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Dan Wolf]], businessman and former state senator<ref>{{cite news|last=Murphy|first=Matt|title=Cape Senator Wolf sees future service in 'different form'|newspaper=The Patriot Ledger|date=November 9, 2015|url=http://www.patriotledger.com/article/20151109/news/151106428}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2016/03/14/state-senator-dan-wolf-readying-gubernatorial-bid-against-charlie-baker/g0dRlVdExvF8eKFEawVbHL/story.html|title=Outgoing state senator ponders running against Baker|work=[[The Boston Globe]]|last=Miller|first=Joshua|date=March 14, 2016|accessdate=July 7, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Joseph Avellone|Joe Avellone]], businessman, former chairman of the [[Wellesley, Massachusetts|Wellesley]] [[Board of selectmen]] and candidate for governor  [[Massachusetts gubernatorial election, 2014|in 2014]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Joshua|title=Joe Avellone, candidate for governor in '14, open to another run|newspaper=The Boston Globe|date=June 8, 2015|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2015/06/08/joe-avellone-candidate-for-governor-open-another-run/5K4akVJURMzY0cc8PP7gQN/story.html}}</ref>\n*[[Quentin Palfrey]], Former Candidate for Lt. Governor <ref>https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2017/08/23/far-only-one-democrat-openly-eyeing-this-statewide-race/LJ6owjVwPH0mDP9JAwWvxL/story.html</ref>\n*[[Ayanna Pressley]], U.S. Representative for [[Massachusetts's 7th congressional district]] and former Boston City Councilor<ref>https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2017/08/23/far-only-one-democrat-openly-eyeing-this-statewide-race/LJ6owjVwPH0mDP9JAwWvxL/story.html</ref>\n\n====Potential Lt. Governor Candidates====\n* Patrick McDermott, [[Norfolk County, Massachusetts|Norfolk County]] Register of Probate and Current Candidate for Norfolk County Sheriff<ref name=openlyeyeing>{{cite news|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2017/08/23/far-only-one-democrat-openly-eyeing-this-statewide-race/LJ6owjVwPH0mDP9JAwWvxL/story.html|title=So far, only one Democrat is openly eyeing this statewide race.|work=[[The Boston Globe]]|last=O'Sullivan|first=Jim|date=August 23, 2017|accessdate=August 30, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Paul Mark]], state representative<ref>https://www.recorder.com/Mark-for-gov-12134709</ref>\n* Jon Mitchell, Mayor of [[New Bedford, Massachusetts|New Bedford]]<ref name=openlyeyeing/>\n* [[Matt O'Malley]], [[Boston]] [[Boston City Council|City Councilor]]<ref name=openlyeyeing/>\n\n===Polling===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;text-align:center;\"\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Maura<br>Healey\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Marty<br>Walsh\n! Undecided\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://www.suffolk.edu/-/media/suffolk/documents/academics/research-at-suffolk/suprc/polls/massachusetts2/2019/6_11_2019_marginals_pdftxt.pdf Suffolk University]\n| June 5\u20139, 2019\n| 370\n| \u00b1 5.1%\n| 34%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}| '''36%'''\n| 28%\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2022 United States elections}}\n{{Massachusetts elections}}\n\n[[Category:Massachusetts gubernatorial elections|2022]]\n[[Category:2022 United States gubernatorial elections|Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:2022 Massachusetts elections|Gubernatorial]]\n", "name_user": "-A-M-B-1996-", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePotential:cased venture capitalist and added relevant title from source", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2022_Massachusetts_gubernatorial_election"}
{"title_page": "Amy Macdonald discography", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist       = [[Amy Macdonald (singer)|Amy Macdonald]]\n| Logo         =\n| Image        = Amy Macdonald 2010 1.JPG\n| Caption      = Amy Macdonald at Rix FM Festival in Stockholm.\n| Studio       = 4\n| Singles      = 18\n| Music videos = 19\n}}\n\nThe '''discography''' page of [[Amy Macdonald]], a [[Scotland|Scottish]] rock/folk singer and songwriter from [[Bishopbriggs]], [[East Dunbartonshire]]. Her debut album, ''[[This Is the Life (Amy Macdonald album)|This Is the Life]],'' was released on 30 July 2007 and has sold more than 3 million copies, mainly in [[Europe]]. The album charted at number one on the [[UK Albums Chart]] as well as various other European countries like Switzerland. Her second album ''[[A Curious Thing]]'' was released in March 2010.\n\nHer first single, \"[[Poison Prince]]\", was released on 7 May 2007. Other singles released from ''This is the Life,'' \"[[Mr Rock & Roll]]\" and [[This Is the Life (Amy Macdonald song)|the album's title track]], were also successful, reaching the top 40 of the [[UK Singles Chart]] and enjoying success elsewhere in [[Europe]], particularly [[Germany]]. \"[[L.A. (Amy Macdonald song)|L.A.]]\" and \"[[Run (Amy Macdonald song)|Run]]\" did not chart on the UK Top 40 but were hits elsewhere in Europe.\n\nMacdonald's second studio album, ''[[A Curious Thing]]'', was released in March 2010. The album's lead single, \"[[Don't Tell Me That It's Over]]\", was a modest hit in the [[United Kingdom]], charting at forty-eight on the UK Singles Chart, but did better in Continental Europe, charting as high as six in [[Germany]] and two in [[Belgium]]. The second single, \"[[Spark (Amy Macdonald song)|Spark]]\", failed to chart in the UK, but charted elsewhere in Europe. Further singles were released from the album which saw success in Europe.\n\nMacdonald's third studio album, ''[[Life in a Beautiful Light]]'' was released in June 2012. The album's lead single, \"[[Slow It Down (Amy Macdonald song)|Slow It Down]]\" was a modest hit in the [[United Kingdom]], charting at forty-five on the UK Singles Chart; it also charted in [[Austria]], [[Belgium]], [[Germany]] and [[Switzerland]].\n\nMacdonald's fourth studio album, ''[[Under Stars]]'' was released on 17 February 2017. \"[[Dream On (Amy Macdonald song)|Dream On]]\" was released as the lead single from the album on 6 January 2017.\n\nIn early 2020 Macdonald has been publishing updates on Instagram that she is currently recording her fifth studio album. The release date has yet to be decided.\n\n==Albums==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"12\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[Music recording sales certification|Certifications]]<br><small>([[List of music recording sales certifications|sales thresholds]])</small>\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Sales\n|- \n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br/><ref name=\"UK\">Peak positions in the United Kingdom:\n* For all except where noted: {{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/2895/amy-macdonald/|title=Amy MacDonald|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|work=Officialcharts.com/}}\n* For \"Poison Prince\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/080531cluk.txt|title=New Chart Entries > 31 May 2008|publisher=Zobbel.de|date=2008-05-31}}\n* For \"This Pretty Face\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/100731cluk.txt|title=New Chart Entries > 31 July 2010|publisher=Zobbel.de|date=2010-07-31}}\n* For \"Love Love\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/101016cluk.txt|title=New Chart Entries > 16 October 2010|publisher=Zobbel.de|date=2010-10-16}}\n* For \"Pride\": {{cite web|url=http://www.zobbel.de/cluk/120825cluk.txt|title=New 