{"title_page": "Mark Curtis (SWP member)", "text_new": "'''Mark Stanton Curtis'''<ref name=\"Justia.com\"/> (born 1959)<ref>{{cite news|title=Iowa|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/USAToday/access/55865858.html?dids=55865858:55865858&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Sep+15%2C+1988&author=&pub=USA+TODAY+%28pre-1997+Fulltext%29&desc=IOWA&pqatl=google|accessdate=May 3, 2012|newspaper=USA Today|date=September 15, 1988}}</ref> is a former member of the [[Socialist Workers Party (USA)|American Socialist Workers Party]] (SWP). Curtis was the subject of a defense campaign by the SWP after he was charged and convicted of [[sexual assault|sexually assaulting]] a 15-year-old girl in 1988. The SWP and others of Curtis's defenders claimed that he had been framed by the police due to his politics and his [[trade union]] activities.  Curtis was [[parole]]d in 1996 after serving eight years of a 25-year sentence in Iowa State Penitentiary.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.themilitant.com/1995/5945/5945_1.html |title=12/4/95 - After Seven Year Fight, Mark Curtis Wins Parole |magazine=The Militant |date=December 4, 1995 |accessdate=June 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe SWP claimed that Curtis was arrested, beaten by the police and framed up for his work in organizing a campaign to defend 17 of his co-workers from [[Central America]] who had been seized in an [[Immigration and Naturalization Service|INS]] raid of the [[Des Moines, Iowa|Des Moines]] meatpacking plant at which they worked. Two police officers who arrested Curtis were found guilty of [[battery (crime)|battery]] in 1992 and ordered to pay $11,000 in damages.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.themilitant.com/1996/605/605_24.html |title=2/5/96 - Mark Curtis Defense Committee Prepares To Move To Chicago |magazine=The Militant |date=Feb 5, 1996 |accessdate=April 9, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"Justia.com\">{{cite web|url=http://law.justia.com/cases/federal/appellate-courts/F2/995/125/66518/ |title=995 F.2 125: Mark Stanton Curtis, Appellee, v. City of Des Moines, Iowa; Daniel Dusenberry; Charles R. Wolf, Defendants, Keith Morris; Denise Morris, Appellants. United States Court of Appeals, Eighth Circuit. -995F.2d 125. Submitted Jan 15, 1993. Decided May 28, 1993. Rehearing Denied July 2, 1993 |publisher=Justia.com |accessdate=June 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\nCurtis claimed that he was stopped at a traffic light in Des Moines when a woman approached him, said she was being followed and asked for a ride home. He claims that on arriving at her house he accompanied her to the porch at which point police came from behind, handcuffed him and pulled down his trousers.  \n        \nThe 15-year-old girl, Demetria Morris, said she and her 11-year-old brother were watching television when Curtis knocked on their door asking for directions. According to the girl, Curtis then asked her if her parents were home, she said they were not, and he attacked her and attempted to [[rape]] her. Unbeknownst to Curtis, however, her brother had called the police who arrived on the scene.<ref name=pelka>{{cite news|last=Pelka|first=Fred|title=The Strange Case of Mark Curtis, Victim or Victimizer?|url=http://www.ontheissuesmagazine.com/1991spring/pelka_spring1991.php|accessdate=May 3, 2012|newspaper=On the Issues magazine|date=Spring 1991}}</ref>\n\nThe Morris family was awarded $80,000 in damages after suing Curtis.<ref name=\"Justia.com\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Books==\n*Jayko, Margaret. ''The Frame-Up of Mark Curtis: A Packinghouse Worker's Fight for Justice''. Pathfinder, 1989. {{ISBN|0-87348-545-9}}\n*McLaughlin, Martin. ''The Mark Curtis Hoax: How the Socialist Workers Party Tried to Dupe the Labor Movement''. Mehring, 1990. {{ISBN|0-929087-46-1}}\n*Gaige, John. ''The Stakes in the Worldwide Political Campaign to Defend Mark Curtis''. Mark Curtis Defense Committee, 1991.\n*Crane, Naomi. ''Why Is Mark Curtis Still in Prison?: The Political Frame-Up of a Unionist and Socialist and the Campaign to Free Him''. Pathfinder, 1995. {{ISBN|0-87348-806-7}}\n*Crane, Naomi. ''A Packinghouse Worker's Fight for Justice: The Mark Curtis Story''. Pathfinder, 1996. {{ISBN|9780873488440}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.themilitant.com/1996/6030/6030_14.html Curtis: `Glad To Return To The Class Struggle' ], September 2, 1996 in \"The Militant\".\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Curtis, Mark}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Socialist Workers Party (United States)]]\n[[Category:Leaders of American trade unions]]\n[[Category:American people convicted of child sexual abuse]]\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n", "text_old": "'''Mark Stanton Curtis'''<ref name=\"Justia.com\"/> (born 1959)<ref>{{cite news|title=Iowa|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/USAToday/access/55865858.html?dids=55865858:55865858&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Sep+15%2C+1988&author=&pub=USA+TODAY+%28pre-1997+Fulltext%29&desc=IOWA&pqatl=google|accessdate=May 3, 2012|newspaper=USA Today|date=September 15, 1988}}</ref> is a former member of the [[Socialist Workers Party (USA)|American Socialist Workers Party]] (SWP). Curtis was the subject of a defense campaign by the SWP after he was charged and convicted of [[sexual assault|sexually assaulting]] a 15-year-old girl in 1988. The SWP and others of Curtis's defenders claimed that he had been framed by the police due to his politics and his [[trade union]] activities.  Curtis was [[parole]]d in 1996 after serving eight years of a 25-year sentence in Iowa State Penitentiary.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.themilitant.com/1995/5945/5945_1.html |title=12/4/95 - After Seven Year Fight, Mark Curtis Wins Parole |magazine=The Militant |date=December 4, 1995 |accessdate=June 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe SWP claimed that Curtis was arrested, beaten by the police and framed up for his work in organizing a campaign to defend 17 of his co-workers from [[Central America]] who had been seized in an [[Immigration and Naturalization Service|INS]] raid of the [[Des Moines, Iowa|Des Moines]] meatpacking plant at which they worked. Two police officers who arrested Curtis were found guilty of [[battery (crime)|battery]] in 1992 and ordered to pay $11,000 in damages.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.themilitant.com/1996/605/605_24.html |title=2/5/96 - Mark Curtis Defense Committee Prepares To Move To Chicago |magazine=The Militant |date=Feb 5, 1996 |accessdate=April 9, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"Justia.com\">{{cite web|url=http://law.justia.com/cases/federal/appellate-courts/F2/995/125/66518/ |title=995 F.2 125: Mark Stanton Curtis, Appellee, v. City of Des Moines, Iowa; Daniel Dusenberry; Charles R. Wolf, Defendants, Keith Morris; Denise Morris, Appellants. United States Court of Appeals, Eighth Circuit. -995F.2d 125. Submitted Jan 15, 1993. Decided May 28, 1993. Rehearing Denied July 2, 1993 |publisher=Justia.com |accessdate=June 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\nCurtis claimed that he was stopped at a traffic light in Des Moines when a woman approached him, said she was being followed and asked for a ride home. He claims that on arriving at her house he accompanied her to the porch at which point police came from behind, handcuffed him and pulled down his trousers.  \n        \nThe 15-year-old girl, Demetria Morris, said she and her 11-year-old brother were watching television when Curtis knocked on their door asking for directions. According to the girl, Curtis then asked her if her parents were home, she said they were not, and he attacked her and attempted to [[rape]] her. Unbeknownst to Curtis, however, her brother had called the police who arrived on the scene.<ref name=pelka>{{cite news|last=Pelka|first=Fred|title=The Strange Case of Mark Curtis, Victim or Victimizer?|url=http://www.ontheissuesmagazine.com/1991spring/pelka_spring1991.php|accessdate=May 3, 2012|newspaper=On the Issues magazine|date=Spring 1991}}</ref>\n\nThe Morris family was awarded $80,000 in damages after suing Curtis.<ref name=\"Justia.com\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Books==\n*Jayko, Margaret. ''The Frame-Up of Mark Curtis: A Packinghouse Worker's Fight for Justice''. Pathfinder, 1989. {{ISBN|0-87348-545-9}}\n*McLaughlin, Martin. ''The Mark Curtis Hoax: How the Socialist Workers Party Tried to Dupe the Labor Movement''. Mehring, 1990. {{ISBN|0-929087-46-1}}\n*Gaige, John. ''The Stakes in the Worldwide Political Campaign to Defend Mark Curtis''. Mark Curtis Defense Committee, 1991.\n*Crane, Naomi. ''Why Is Mark Curtis Still in Prison?: The Political Frame-Up of a Unionist and Socialist and the Campaign to Free Him''. Pathfinder, 1995. {{ISBN|0-87348-806-7}}\n*Crane, Naomi. ''A Packinghouse Worker's Fight for Justice: The Mark Curtis Story''. Pathfinder, 1996. {{ISBN|9780873488440}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.themilitant.com/1996/6030/6030_14.html Curtis: `Glad To Return To The Class Struggle' ], September 2, 1996 in \"The Militant\".\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Curtis, Mark}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Socialist Workers Party (United States)]]\n[[Category:Leaders of American trade unions]]\n[[Category:American people convicted of child sexual abuse]]\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_Curtis_(SWP_member)"}
{"title_page": "Shanina Shaik", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox model\n| image         = Shanina Shaik.png\n| image_size    = 200\n| name          = Shanina Shaik\n| caption       = Shaik in 2008\n| birth_name    =\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1991|2|11}}\n| birth_place   = [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]]\n| nationality   = Australian\n| spouse        = {{marriage|DJ Ruckus|2018|2019|end=divorced}}\n| occupation    = Model\n| yearsactive   = 2008\u2013present\n| haircolor     = Dark brown\n| eyecolor      = Green\n| height        = {{height|m=1.73}}\n| agency       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[IMG Models]] (Worldwide)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imgmodels.com/shaninashaik/paris/women|title=Shanina Shaik - IMG Models|publisher=}}</ref>\n* Traffic Models (Barcelona)\n* MIKAs (Stockholm)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/models/shanina-shaik|title=Shanina Shaik - Model|publisher=}}</ref> }}\n}}\n'''Shanina Shaik''' (born 11 February 1991)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.vogue.com.au/people/models/shanina+shaik,113 | title=Shanina Shaik | work=Vogue | accessdate=12 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/shanina_shaik/photos/photos.htm |title=FMD - General Photos of shanina shaik |publisher=Fashionmodeldirectory.com |date=11 February 1991 |accessdate=3 September 2010}}</ref> is an Australian [[model (person)|model]] of Pakistani and Lithuanian ancestry.\n\n==Early life==\nShaik's mother, Kim, whose parents emigrated to Australia after [[World War II]] and met in Australia, is of [[Lithuanian people|Lithuanian]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220083750/https://www.theweeklyreview.com.au/meet/shanina-shaik-the-aussie-model-on-a-global-trajectory/|archive-date=February 20, 2018|url=https://www.theweeklyreview.com.au/meet/shanina-shaik-the-aussie-model-on-a-global-trajectory/|title=Shanina Shaik; the Aussie model on a global trajectory|publisher=The Weekly Review|url-status=dead}}</ref> Her father Hanif, who was born in Singapore, is of [[Pakistani people|Pakistani]] and [[Saudi Arabian]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/models/shanina-shaik|title=Shanina Shaik - Model|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"ny\">{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2011/11/meet-the-new-girl-shanina-shaik.html#|title=Meet the New Girl: Shanina Shaik Bonded With Miranda Kerr at the Victoria\u2019s Secret Fashion Show|last=Lim|first=James|date=17 November 2011|publisher=[[New York Magazine]]|accessdate=18 November 2011}}</ref> She started modeling when she was eight years old for Myer and appearing in a TV commercial for Hyundai, but stopped when she started high school and got accepted into an accelerated program, graduating a year before her classmates. At the age of fifteen, encouraged by others, she entered the Girlfriend Model Competition. While agents were interested in her, she was too young to move to [[Sydney]], so she went on to participate on the Australian reality show ''[[Make Me a Supermodel (Australian TV series)|Make Me A Supermodel]]'',<ref name=\"ny\"/> finishing as the runner-up.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/celebrity/make-me-a-supermodels-shanina-shaik-is-all-sex-martin-walsh/story-e6frfmqr-1111118030211|title=Make Me A Supermodel's Shanina Shaik is all sex - Martin Walsh|date=14 November 2008|publisher=News Limited.|page=1|accessdate=11 September 2010}}</ref>\nShaik was raised [[Muslim]]. Speaking about her upbringing in 2016, Shaik reflected: \u201cI was born and raised Muslim and I lived a very normal lifestyle. My father is very open to my job and understanding and he is grateful for the woman I have become. I'm a very sophisticated and respectful woman. I had a great upbringing and a great lifestyle with my sibling.\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.albawaba.com/entertainment/victorias-secret-angel-shanina-shaik-her-muslim-upbringing-836082|title=Victoria's Secret Angel Shanina Shaik on her Muslim upbringing|last=|first=|date=3 May 2016|work=albawaba |access-date=21 February 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn her debut season during the Autumn/Winter 2009 season Shaik walked over 8 shows in New York City. She opened [[Yeohlee]] and walked for other designers such as Shipley & Halmos, [[Abaete]], Mara Hoffman, Lorick, [[Project Runway]], [[Trovata]] and Richie Rich.{{Citation needed|date=September 2010}} In her second season, she scored a show card for the Spring/Summer 2010. Following this she walked for designers [[Betsey Johnson]], [[Catherine Malandrino]], Gerlan Jeans, Nary Manivong, Rachel Antonoff and Susan Woo. During the Autumn/Winter 2010 season Shanina walked for Bebe by Kardashian, Emu Australia, Iodice and [[Project Runway]].\n\nShaik has appeared in catalogues for [[Macy's]], [[Alloy]], [[Avon Products|Avon]], Intermix, [[Urban Outfitters]], [[Lovable]], Burda Style, Spiegel, [[Free People]], [[Bloomingdales]], [[J. C. Penney]], Seafolly, Otto, Shop Bop, Sasha Samuel and [[Ann Taylor (clothing retailer)|Ann Taylor]]. Her advertisements include [[A\u00e9ropostale (clothing)|A\u00e9ropostale]], Cotton On, [[Olay]] [[New Look (clothing retailer)|New Look]], Burneo Chocolate, Body & Bath Works 'Dark Kiss' fragrance, Edward Joseph, Imari by Avon, [[General Pants Co.]], [[Bonds (company)|Bonds]], [[Bauhaus]] and Matrix Hair Biolage<ref>[http://www.womenfitness.net/news/other/victoriaSecret_routine.htm \"Victoria's Secret model Shanina Shaik gets to her exercise routine\"] Retrieved 29 May 2015</ref>\n\nShortly after signing with New York Model Management, Shaik appeared in editorials for ''[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen Magazine]]'' and ''[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]''. Other appearances include ''Level Magazine'', ''Orlando Style Magazine'', ''2 Wheeler Tuner Magazine'', ''Philadelphia Style Magazine'', ''Tu Style'' and ''Zink Magazine''.\n\nIn 2010, Shaik walked in the Spring/Summer 2011 catwalk show for [[Project Runway]] and L.A.M.B.\n\nIn 2011, she switched to [[NEXT Model Management]],<ref name=\"ny\"/> and from Chadwick Model Management to Chic Model Management. She starred in a campaign for Italian lingerie giant [[Intimissimi]] and Australian shoe brand RMK. Shaik has worked for other brands such as Macy's, Avon, Bloomingdales, Free People, Olay, Seafolly, Spiegel, J. C. Penney and Sasha Samuel. She also starred at Rosemount Australian Fashion Week Spring/Summer 2012 walking for Bless'ed Are The Meek, Guanabana, Karen Neilson, Kirrily Johnston, L.A.M.B., Lisa Blue, Lisa Marie, Miss Unkon, None the Richer, Nookie Beach, Project Runway, Roopa Pemmaraju, Terri Donna, Wonders Cease.\n\nShaik scored a breakthrough when she was cast to walk in the 2011 [[Victoria's Secret Fashion Show]],<ref name=\"ny\"/> making her the sixth Australian along with [[Miranda Kerr]], [[Jessica Hart (model)|Jessica Hart]], [[Elyse Taylor]], [[Sarah Stephens]], and [[Abbey Lee Kershaw]] to star in the show. Shaik has also walked for [[Chanel]]'s Pre-Fall 2012 collection at the [[Grand Palais]] in [[Paris]].\n\nIn 2012, Shaik appeared in print-work for [[Victoria's Secret]] and [[Bonds (company)|Bonds]]. During Fall/Winter 2012 Fashion Week she opened [[Jason Wu]], and also walked for Ruffian, Kevork Kiledjian, [[Charlotte Ronson]], [[Nanette Lepore]], [[Diesel (brand)|Diesel]], [[Oscar de la Renta]], [[L'Wren Scott]], [[Tom Ford]], [[Blumarine]], Atsuro Tayama, Maiyet, [[Vivienne Westwood]], and [[Stella McCartney]]. Shaik also did a shoot with ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' Australia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://forums.thefashionspot.com/f52/shanina-shaik-154835-11.html|title=Shanina Shaik (November 2011 - February 2013) - Page 11 - the Fashion Spot|website=forums.thefashionspot.com}}</ref> She is also an ambassador for [[Just Jeans]] and has modeled alongside rugby star [[Sonny Bill Williams]]. In 2016, Shaik became a brand ambassador for [http://blog.seafolly.com/au/meet-shanina Australian swimwear brand Seafolly].\n\nShaik was featured on the covers of ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'', ''[[Cleo (magazine)|Cleo]]'', ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' India, ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'' Singapore, Arabia, Vietnam and Australia.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hey, Shanina!|url=http://www.cleo.com.au/celebrity/celebrity-news/2014/1/cleo-cover-girl-shanina-shaik/|accessdate=7 July 2015|work=[[Cleo (magazine)|Cleo]]|date=20 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Shanina Shaik and Chip the koala are our April cover stars |url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com.au/news/fashion-buzz/2015/3/shanina-shaik-and-koala-for-bazaar-april-2015/|accessdate=7 July 2015|work=Harper's Bazaar|date=9 March 2015}}</ref> In 2019, she appeared on the May/June cover of ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.maxim.com/women/shanina-shaik-instagram-2019-4|title=BEHOLD MAXIM COVER MODEL SHANINA SHAIK'S MOST STUNNING INSTAGRAMS|work=Maxim}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nShaik got engaged to her boyfriend of eight months Gregory \u201cDJ Ruckus\u201d Andrews in December 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/style/shanina-shaik-on-her-engagement-to-dj-ruckus-it-was-quick-but-it-feels-right/|title=Shanina Shaik on Her Engagement to DJ Ruckus: 'It Was Quick, But It Feels Right'|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> They married in the [[The Bahamas|Bahamas]] on April 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brides.com/story/shanina-shaik-dj-ruckus-are-engaged-her-hexagonal-diamond-ring|title=Shanina Shaik and DJ Ruckus Are Engaged! See Her Hexagonal Diamond Ring|website=brides|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> They separated in June 2019,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/style/shanina-shaik-husband-greg-dj-ruckus-andrews-separate-after-year-marriage/|title=Shanina Shaik and Husband Greg 'D.J. Ruckus' Andrews Separate After One Year of Marriage|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> and Shaik filed for divorce a month later after a year of marriage.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/style/shanina-shaik-files-divorce-husband-dj-ruckus/|title=Shanina Shaik Files for Divorce Nearly 1 Month After Separating from Husband DJ Ruckus|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{fashionmodel}}\n*{{models.com}}\n\n{{2010-2019VSFashion Show}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shaik, Shanina}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Australian female models]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Lithuanian descent]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Pakistani descent]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Saudi Arabian descent]]\n[[Category:Models from Melbourne]]\n[[Category:IMG Models models]]\n[[Category:Australian models of Pakistani descent]]\n[[Category:Australian Muslims]]\n[[Category:Female models from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Muslim models]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox model\n| image         = Shanina Shaik.png\n| image_size    = 200\n| name          = Shanina Shaik\n| caption       = Shaik in 2008\n| birth_name    =\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1991|2|11}}\n| birth_place   = [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]]\n| nationality   = Australian\n| spouse        = {{marriage|DJ Ruckus|2018|2019|end=divorced}}\n| occupation    = Model\n| yearsactive   = 2008\u2013present\n| haircolor     = Dark brown\n| eyecolor      = Green\n| height        = {{height|m=1.73}}\n| agency       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[IMG Models]] (Worldwide)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imgmodels.com/shaninashaik/paris/women|title=Shanina Shaik - IMG Models|publisher=}}</ref>\n* Traffic Models (Barcelona)\n* MIKAs (Stockholm)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/models/shanina-shaik|title=Shanina Shaik - Model|publisher=}}</ref> }}\n}}\n'''Shanina Shaik''' (born 11 February 1991)<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.vogue.com.au/people/models/shanina+shaik,113 | title=Shanina Shaik | work=Vogue | accessdate=12 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/shanina_shaik/photos/photos.htm |title=FMD - General Photos of shanina shaik |publisher=Fashionmodeldirectory.com |date=11 February 1991 |accessdate=3 September 2010}}</ref> is an Australian [[model (person)|model]] of Pakistani and Lithuanian ancestry.\n\n==Early life==\nShaik's mother, Kim, whose parents emigrated to Australia after [[World War II]] and met in Australia, is of [[Lithuanian people|Lithuanian]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220083750/https://www.theweeklyreview.com.au/meet/shanina-shaik-the-aussie-model-on-a-global-trajectory/|archive-date=February 20, 2018|url=https://www.theweeklyreview.com.au/meet/shanina-shaik-the-aussie-model-on-a-global-trajectory/|title=Shanina Shaik; the Aussie model on a global trajectory|publisher=The Weekly Review|url-status=dead}}</ref> Her father Hanif, who was born in Singapore, is of [[Pakistani people|Pakistani]] and [[Saudi Arabian]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/models/shanina-shaik|title=Shanina Shaik - Model|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"ny\">{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2011/11/meet-the-new-girl-shanina-shaik.html#|title=Meet the New Girl: Shanina Shaik Bonded With Miranda Kerr at the Victoria\u2019s Secret Fashion Show|last=Lim|first=James|date=17 November 2011|publisher=[[New York Magazine]]|accessdate=18 November 2011}}</ref> She started modeling when she was 8 years old for Myer and appearing in a TV commercial for Hyundai, but stopped when she started high school and got accepted into an accelerated program, graduating a year before her classmates. At the age of fifteen, encouraged by others, she entered the Girlfriend Model Competition. While agents were interested in her, she was too young to move to [[Sydney]], so she went on to participate on the Australian reality show ''[[Make Me a Supermodel (Australian TV series)|Make Me A Supermodel]]'',<ref name=\"ny\"/> finishing as the runner-up.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/celebrity/make-me-a-supermodels-shanina-shaik-is-all-sex-martin-walsh/story-e6frfmqr-1111118030211|title=Make Me A Supermodel's Shanina Shaik is all sex - Martin Walsh|date=14 November 2008|publisher=News Limited.|page=1|accessdate=11 September 2010}}</ref>\nShaik was raised [[Muslim]]. Speaking about her upbringing in 2016, Shaik reflected: \u201cI was born and raised Muslim and I lived a very normal lifestyle. My father is very open to my job and understanding and he is grateful for the woman I have become. I'm a very sophisticated and respectful woman. I had a great upbringing and a great lifestyle with my sibling.\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.albawaba.com/entertainment/victorias-secret-angel-shanina-shaik-her-muslim-upbringing-836082|title=Victoria's Secret Angel Shanina Shaik on her Muslim upbringing|last=|first=|date=3 May 2016|work=albawaba |access-date=21 February 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn her debut season during the Autumn/Winter 2009 season Shaik walked over 8 shows in New York City. She opened [[Yeohlee]] and walked for other designers such as Shipley & Halmos, [[Abaete]], Mara Hoffman, Lorick, [[Project Runway]], [[Trovata]] and Richie Rich.{{Citation needed|date=September 2010}} In her second season, she scored a show card for the Spring/Summer 2010. Following this she walked for designers [[Betsey Johnson]], [[Catherine Malandrino]], Gerlan Jeans, Nary Manivong, Rachel Antonoff and Susan Woo. During the Autumn/Winter 2010 season Shanina walked for Bebe by Kardashian, Emu Australia, Iodice and [[Project Runway]].\n\nShaik has appeared in catalogues for [[Macy's]], [[Alloy]], [[Avon Products|Avon]], Intermix, [[Urban Outfitters]], [[Lovable]], Burda Style, Spiegel, [[Free People]], [[Bloomingdales]], [[J. C. Penney]], Seafolly, Otto, Shop Bop, Sasha Samuel and [[Ann Taylor (clothing retailer)|Ann Taylor]]. Her advertisements include [[A\u00e9ropostale (clothing)|A\u00e9ropostale]], Cotton On, [[Olay]] [[New Look (clothing retailer)|New Look]], Burneo Chocolate, Body & Bath Works 'Dark Kiss' fragrance, Edward Joseph, Imari by Avon, [[General Pants Co.]], [[Bonds (company)|Bonds]], [[Bauhaus]] and Matrix Hair Biolage<ref>[http://www.womenfitness.net/news/other/victoriaSecret_routine.htm \"Victoria's Secret model Shanina Shaik gets to her exercise routine\"] Retrieved 29 May 2015</ref>\n\nShortly after signing with New York Model Management, Shaik appeared in editorials for ''[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen Magazine]]'' and ''[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]''. Other appearances include ''Level Magazine'', ''Orlando Style Magazine'', ''2 Wheeler Tuner Magazine'', ''Philadelphia Style Magazine'', ''Tu Style'' and ''Zink Magazine''.\n\nIn 2010, Shaik walked in the Spring/Summer 2011 catwalk show for [[Project Runway]] and L.A.M.B.\n\nIn 2011, she switched to [[NEXT Model Management]],<ref name=\"ny\"/> and from Chadwick Model Management to Chic Model Management. She starred in a campaign for Italian lingerie giant [[Intimissimi]] and Australian shoe brand RMK. Shaik has worked for other brands such as Macy's, Avon, Bloomingdales, Free People, Olay, Seafolly, Spiegel, J. C. Penney and Sasha Samuel. She also starred at Rosemount Australian Fashion Week Spring/Summer 2012 walking for Bless'ed Are The Meek, Guanabana, Karen Neilson, Kirrily Johnston, L.A.M.B., Lisa Blue, Lisa Marie, Miss Unkon, None the Richer, Nookie Beach, Project Runway, Roopa Pemmaraju, Terri Donna, Wonders Cease.\n\nShaik scored a breakthrough when she was cast to walk in the 2011 [[Victoria's Secret Fashion Show]],<ref name=\"ny\"/> making her the sixth Australian along with [[Miranda Kerr]], [[Jessica Hart (model)|Jessica Hart]], [[Elyse Taylor]], [[Sarah Stephens]], and [[Abbey Lee Kershaw]] to star in the show. Shaik has also walked for [[Chanel]]'s Pre-Fall 2012 collection at the [[Grand Palais]] in [[Paris]].\n\nIn 2012, Shaik appeared in print-work for [[Victoria's Secret]] and [[Bonds (company)|Bonds]]. During Fall/Winter 2012 Fashion Week she opened [[Jason Wu]], and also walked for Ruffian, Kevork Kiledjian, [[Charlotte Ronson]], [[Nanette Lepore]], [[Diesel (brand)|Diesel]], [[Oscar de la Renta]], [[L'Wren Scott]], [[Tom Ford]], [[Blumarine]], Atsuro Tayama, Maiyet, [[Vivienne Westwood]], and [[Stella McCartney]]. Shaik also did a shoot with ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' Australia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://forums.thefashionspot.com/f52/shanina-shaik-154835-11.html|title=Shanina Shaik (November 2011 - February 2013) - Page 11 - the Fashion Spot|website=forums.thefashionspot.com}}</ref> She is also an ambassador for [[Just Jeans]] and has modeled alongside rugby star [[Sonny Bill Williams]]. In 2016, Shaik became a brand ambassador for [http://blog.seafolly.com/au/meet-shanina Australian swimwear brand Seafolly].\n\nShaik was featured on the covers of ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'', ''[[Cleo (magazine)|Cleo]]'', ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' India, ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'' Singapore, Arabia, Vietnam and Australia.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hey, Shanina!|url=http://www.cleo.com.au/celebrity/celebrity-news/2014/1/cleo-cover-girl-shanina-shaik/|accessdate=7 July 2015|work=[[Cleo (magazine)|Cleo]]|date=20 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Shanina Shaik and Chip the koala are our April cover stars |url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com.au/news/fashion-buzz/2015/3/shanina-shaik-and-koala-for-bazaar-april-2015/|accessdate=7 July 2015|work=Harper's Bazaar|date=9 March 2015}}</ref> In 2019, she appeared on the May/June cover of ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.maxim.com/women/shanina-shaik-instagram-2019-4|title=BEHOLD MAXIM COVER MODEL SHANINA SHAIK'S MOST STUNNING INSTAGRAMS|work=Maxim}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nShaik got engaged to her boyfriend of eight months Gregory \u201cDJ Ruckus\u201d Andrews in December 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/style/shanina-shaik-on-her-engagement-to-dj-ruckus-it-was-quick-but-it-feels-right/|title=Shanina Shaik on Her Engagement to DJ Ruckus: 'It Was Quick, But It Feels Right'|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> They married in the [[The Bahamas|Bahamas]] on April 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brides.com/story/shanina-shaik-dj-ruckus-are-engaged-her-hexagonal-diamond-ring|title=Shanina Shaik and DJ Ruckus Are Engaged! See Her Hexagonal Diamond Ring|website=brides|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> They separated in June 2019,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/style/shanina-shaik-husband-greg-dj-ruckus-andrews-separate-after-year-marriage/|title=Shanina Shaik and Husband Greg 'D.J. Ruckus' Andrews Separate After One Year of Marriage|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> and Shaik filed for divorce a month later after a year of marriage.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/style/shanina-shaik-files-divorce-husband-dj-ruckus/|title=Shanina Shaik Files for Divorce Nearly 1 Month After Separating from Husband DJ Ruckus|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{fashionmodel}}\n*{{models.com}}\n\n{{2010-2019VSFashion Show}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shaik, Shanina}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Australian female models]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Lithuanian descent]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Pakistani descent]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Saudi Arabian descent]]\n[[Category:Models from Melbourne]]\n[[Category:IMG Models models]]\n[[Category:Australian models of Pakistani descent]]\n[[Category:Australian Muslims]]\n[[Category:Female models from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Muslim models]]\n", "name_user": "Kbabej", "label": "safe", "comment": "Spell out", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shanina_Shaik"}
{"title_page": "Adriana Lima", "text_new": "{{pp-move-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{Short description|Brazilian model and actress}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name         = Adriana Lima\n| image        = Adriana Lima 2019 by Glenn Francis.jpg\n| caption      = Lima in July 2019\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1981|6|12}}\n| birth_place  = [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]], [[Bahia]], [[Brazil]]\n| occupation   = {{hlist|Model|actress}}\n| years_active = 1996\u2013present\n| height       = {{convert|1.78|m|ftin|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"fmd\">{{cite web|url=https://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/Adriana_Lima|title=Adriana Lima - Fashion Model|work=Fashion Model Directory|accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"models.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.models.com/models/Adriana-Lima|title=Adriana Lima - Model Profile - Photos & latest news|work=Models.com|accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n| haircolor    = Dark Brown<ref name=\"fmd\"/><ref name=\"models.com\"/>\n| eyecolor     = Blue<ref name=\"fmd\"/><ref name=\"models.com\"/>\n| spouse       = {{marriage|[[Marko Jari\u0107]]|2009|2016|reason=divorced}}\n| children     = 2\n| agency       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Creative Artists Agency]] (New York, Los Angeles)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/adriana-lima-signs-with-caa-1203234766/|title=Adriana Lima Signs With Creative Artists Agency|work=WWD|date=August 7, 2019|accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Elite Model Management]] (Paris, London, Milan)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.models.com/models/Adriana-Lima|title=Adriana Lima - Model|publisher=}}</ref>\n}}\n| website      = {{URL|http://www.adrianalima.com/|www.AdrianaLima.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Adriana Lima'''<ref name=\"Full name\">{{YouTube|lO4d-Mxvb3Q|W Radio Colombia Interview - Part 1}}</ref> ({{IPA-pt|ad\u027ei\u02c8\u00e3n\u0250 \u02c8lim\u0250|br}}; born June 12, 1981) is a Brazilian [[Model (person)|model]] and actress, best known as a [[Victoria's Secret Angel]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.victoriassecret.ca/vsallaccess/angels/adriana-lima|title=Adriana Lima - Victoria's Secret|work=[[Victoria's Secret]]|accessdate=January 17, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190117070150/https://www.victoriassecret.ca/vsallaccess/angels/adriana-lima|archivedate=January 17, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> from 1999 to 2018.<ref name=\"People\">{{cite web|url=https://people.com/style/victorias-secret-fashion-show-adriana-lima/|title=7 Reasons Adriana Lima Is the Guardian Angel of the Victoria's Secret Fashion Show|last=Talarico|first=Brittany|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=December 5, 2016|accessdate=October 1, 2018}}</ref> She was the longest-running model and named \"the most valuable Victoria's Secret Angel\" in 2017. She is also known as a spokesmodel for [[Maybelline]] cosmetics since 2003, and for her [[Super Bowl]] and [[Kia Motors]] commercials. At age 15, Lima won [[Ford Models|Ford]]'s \"Supermodel of Brazil\" competition, and took second place the following year in the Ford \"[[Supermodel of the World (contest)|Supermodel of the World]]\" competition before signing with [[Elite Model Management]] in [[New York City]].\n\nLima is currently ranked by models.com as one of the \"[[Supermodels|New Supers]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/rankings/ui/NewSupers/|title=The New Supers List|work=Models.com|accessdate=February 20, 2017}}</ref> Since 2014, Lima has been the world's second highest-paid model. In 2012, she came in 4th place on the ''[[Forbes]]'' top-earning models list, estimated to have earned $7.3 million in one year. In 2013, she came in 3rd place and in 2014 she came in 2nd place with earnings of $8 million. In 2015, she came in 2nd place with earnings of $9 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/briansolomon/2012/06/14/the-worlds-highest-paid-models/|title=The World's Highest Paid Models|last=Solomon|first=Brian|work=[[Forbes]]|date=June 14, 2012|accessdate=June 20, 2012}}</ref> In 2016, she kept the second place with earnings of {{US$|10.5 million|link=yes}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2016/08/30/the-worlds-highest-paid-models-2016-karlie-kloss-and-kendall-jenner-storm-top-three-with-10-million-apiece/|title=The World's Highest Paid Models 2016|last=Robehmed|first=Natalie|work=[[Forbes]]|date=August 30, 2016|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nLima has served as brand ambassador for the clothing brand [[Desigual]] based in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]], for the Beachwear collection of Italian brand [[Calzedonia]], and for the ready-to-wear collection of Italian brand [[Sportmax]]. She is currently an ambassador for [[International Watch Company|IWC]], [[Puma (brand)|Puma]], and [[Chopard]].\n\n==Early life==\nLima was born on 12 June 1981 in [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador, Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instyle.com/celebrity/adriana-limas-birthday-serenade-will-give-you-goosebumps|title=Adriana Lima's Birthday Serenade Will Give You Goosebumps|last=Berg|first=Jenny|work=[[InStyle]]|date=June 13, 2017|accessdate=June 15, 2019}}</ref> Many sources stated that \"Francesca\" is her middle name, but Lima herself denied this in an interview to [[W Radio (Colombia)|W Radio Colombia]] in 2010, and confirmed that her name is only Adriana Lima.<ref name=\"Full name\"/> Her parents are Nelson Torres, a carpenter,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ego.globo.com/Gente/Noticias/0,,MUL327087-9798,00-ADRIANA+LIMA+DESCOBRE+QUE+O+PAI+FOI+SEU+IRMAO+EM+VIDA+PASSADA.html|title=Adriana Lima descobre que o pai foi seu irm\u00e3o em vida passada|last=Tecidio|first=Luciana|work=EGO.Globo.com|language=Portuguese|date=May 25, 2007}}</ref> and Maria das Gra\u00e7as Lima, a social worker.<ref name=\"ISTO\u00c9\">{{cite web|url=http://www.terra.com.br/istoegente/211/reportagens/capa_adriana_lima_02.htm|title=A princesa da moda|work=ISTO\u00c9 Gente|language=Portuguese|date=August 18, 2003|accessdate=November 24, 2016}}</ref> Her father left the family when she was six months old, and Lima was raised only by her mother.<ref name=\"ISTO\u00c9\"/>\n\nLima is of [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]], [[Swiss people|Swiss]], [[Native Brazilian]], [[Japanese people|Japanese]], [[Ethnic groups of Africa|African]] and [[West Indian]] descent<ref name=\"25things\">{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/lifestyle/fashion/25-things-you-may-not-know-about-victorias-secret-angel-adriana-lima/ss-BBjKo8E#image=22|title=25 things you may not know about Adriana Lima|work=MSN|date=May 14, 2015|accessdate=October 1, 2019}}</ref> (which classifies her as a [[Pardo Brazilians|Pardo Brazilian]]).<!-- Note: Do not remove this Brazilian demographic classification. -->{{efn|group=note|English translated sources and Lima herself states she has \"Indian\" ancestry. The ambiguous meaning of the word \"Indian\" in English, has led some to believe that the Amerindian \"indian\" ancestry originated from India, when in slang \"indian\" is meant to refer to indigenous peoples of the Americas. In Portuguese, such ambiguity is nonexistent, since there are two words to convey the different meanings: ''[[wikt:\u00edndio|\u00edndio]]'' for an [[Native Americans in the United States|American Indian]] (or [[Amerindian]], including Native Brazilians); and ''[[wikt:indiano#Portuguese|indiano]]'' for people and things related to India.}} But she considers herself [[Afro-Brazilian]].<ref>{{YouTube|id=k1sSbW61pdI|title=Adriana Lima talks about her mixed heritage}}</ref>\n\nLima speaks four languages: her native [[Brazilian Portuguese|Portuguese]], [[English language|English]], [[Italian language|Italian]], and [[Spanish language|Spanish]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vogue.it/en/encyclo/people/l/adriana-lima|title=Adriana Lima|publisher=Vogue Italy|accessdate=February 20, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151102024543/http://www.vogue.it/en/encyclo/people/l/adriana-lima|archivedate=November 2, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Adriana Lima by David Shankbone Cropped.JPG|left|thumb|upright|Lima at the premiere of ''[[Spider-Man 3]]'' at the [[Tribeca Film Festival]] in [[Queens]], [[New York City]] in 2007]]\nLima never thought about being a model, although she had won many beauty pageants in elementary school.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/adriana-lima-pictures_n_1582001|title=Adriana Lima's Style Evolution: From Brazilian Beauty Queen To Victoria's Secret Angel (PHOTOS)|last=Leon|first=Sarah|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=October 11, 2012|quote=Although today she is one of the highest-paid models in the world, Lima got her start competing in beauty pageants in her native Brazil.}}</ref> However, a friend at school who wanted to enter a modeling contest and did not want to enter alone, so Lima entered with her. Both sent in pictures, and the contest sponsor soon asked Lima to come out for the competition. Soon after, at age 15, she entered and finished in first place in Ford's \"Supermodel of Brazil\" model search. She subsequently entered the 1996 [[Ford Models Supermodel of the World]] contest and finished in second place.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.de/models/adriana-lima|title=Adriana Lima: Model-Portrait|publisher=Elle Germany|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref> Three years later, Lima moved to New York City and signed with [[Elite Model Management]].<ref name=\"Insider\">{{cite web|url=https://www.insider.com/adriana-limas-modeling-career-timeline-2018-11|title=Adriana Lima is hanging up her Victoria's Secret wings \u2014 here's a look back at her modeling career|last=Ngomsi|first=Vinciane|work=[[Insider Inc.]]|date=November 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHer first magazine cover was [[Marie Claire|Marie Claire Brazil]] in September 1998. Her first [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] covers were the Italian ''Vogue Gioiello'' in September 2000, on their 20th Anniversary issue, and Vogue Brasil the next month.<ref name=\"Insider\"/>\n\nAs a runway model, she has walked the catwalk for designers such as Rosa Cha, Blue man, Fashion's Night Out, Caio Gobbi, Fause Haten, M. Officer, Luca Luca, Liverpool Fashion, Dosso Dossi, Carmen Steffens, C\u00eda Maritima, Agua de Coco, Lino Villaventura, Forum, Vassarette, Zoomp, Joan Vass, Cori, [[Emilio Pucci]], [[Fendi]], [[Giles Deacon]], [[Carmen Marc Valvo]], [[Emanuel Ungaro]], [[Baby Phat]], [[Giorgio Armani]], [[Pierre Balmain|Balmain]], [[Bottega Veneta]], [[Sportmax]], [[Vera Wang]], [[Valentino Garavani|Valentino]], [[Miu Miu]], [[Givenchy]], [[Versace]], [[Cividini]], [[Alexandre Herchcovitch]], [[Jason Wu]], [[Marc Jacobs]], [[Christian Dior]], [[Paco Rabanne]], [[Victoria's Secret]], [[Sean John]], [[Prada]], [[Louis Vuitton]], [[Desigual]], [[Cynthia Rowley]], [[Sully Bonnelly]], [[Anna Sui]], [[Guy Laroche]], [[John Galliano]], [[Alexander McQueen]], [[Yigal Azrou\u00ebl]], [[Ralph Lauren]], [[Christian Lacroix]], [[Escada]], [[Nanette Lepore]], [[Richard Tyler (designer)|Richard Tyler]], [[Triton (fashion)|Triton]], and [[Betsey Johnson]].\n\nLima became a [[Guess (clothing)|GUESS?]] girl in 2000, appearing in that year's fall ad campaign. She also appeared in the book ''A Second Decade of Guess? Images''.<ref name=\"Insider\"/>\n\nLima continued to build upon her portfolio, doing more print work for [[Maybelline]], for whom she has worked as a spokesmodel since 2003 to 2009; Also in the same year, she appeared in the company's first calendar and did an ad campaign for [[Swatch]]. Lima has also worked for notable fashion brands [[Bebe Stores|bebe]], [[Armani]], [[Versace]], [[De Beers]], [[Elie Saab]], [[Colcci]], [[Elsa Schiaparelli|Schiaparelli]], [[Prada]], [[Intimissimi]], [[Guess (clothing)|GUESS?]], [[LOEWE (fashion brand)|LOEWE]], [[H&M]], [[Bulgari]], [[Miu Miu]], [[DKNY]], [[Emporio Armani]], [[Givenchy]], [[Keds (shoes)|Keds]], [[Mossimo]], [[Jason Wu]], [[Balmain (fashion house)|Balmain]], [[Blumarine]], [[Marc Jacobs]], [[Maybelline]], [[Max Azria|BCBG]], and [[Louis Vuitton]].\n\nShe also appeared on the covers and in the editorials of other fashion magazines such as ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'', ''[[Elle (magazine)|ELLE]]'', ''[[Grazia]]'', ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'', ''[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]'', ''[[GQ]]'', ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'', ''[[Arena (magazine)|Arena]]'', ''[[V (American magazine)|V]]'', ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]'', ''[[Garage Magazine|Garage]]'', and ''French Revue des Modes''.\n\nHer April 2006 ''GQ'' cover was the highest-selling issue of that magazine for the year.<ref name=\"Forbes models\"/> It was also one of the all-time best selling issues of the publication.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/rankings/ui/TopSexiest/1545#1545|title=MODELS.com's Top Sexiest Models - 5-1|work=Models.com|date=August 12, 2011|accessdate=September 26, 2019}}</ref> The magazine named her \"The World's Most Voluptuous Virgin\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2006/03/16/limas-choice|title=Adriana Lima's new title is \"the world's most voluptuous virgin\"|work=Vogue UK|date=March 16, 2006|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Victoria's Secret models visit Guantanamo, December 2007.jpg|thumb|Victoria's Secret Angels Lima (left), [[Marisa Miller]] and [[Selita Ebanks]] ride in the [[Guantanamo Bay Naval Base|Guantanamo Bay]] Christmas Parade on December 1, 2007 in a [[Cadillac Eldorado]]]]\n\nIn 2006, Lima ranked as the fifth highest paid supermodel. Between 2007 and 2008, she ranked as the world's fourth highest paid supermodel by Forbes Magazine.<ref name=\"Forbes models\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/2007/07/09/models-media-bundchen-biz-media-cz_kb_0716topmodels1_slide.html#7de7ae926a24|title=In Pictures: The World's Top-Earning Models|last=Blakeley|first=Kiri|work=[[Forbes]]|date=July 16, 2007|accessdate=April 8, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"teleuk\">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?xml=/news/2007/07/16/wforbes116.xml |title=Forbes Top Fifteen Models |newspaper=Telegraph|date=July 16, 2007}}</ref><ref name=\"f06\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2006/53/C3P8.html|title=Top 100 Celebrities 2006|work=Forbes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/2008/04/30/models-bundchen-klum-biz-media-cz_kb_0430topmodels_slide_8.html|title=In Pictures: The World's 15 Top-Earning Models|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 30, 2008|accessdate=December 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, she again fronted the cover of GQ, this time attracting a record number of visits to the publication's website. She also appeared in the 2005 [[Pirelli Calendar]] and became the face of Italy's cell phone carrier, [[Telecom Italia Mobile]], a move that earned her the nickname, \"the [[Catherine Zeta-Jones]] of Italy.\"<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2005/53/C3P8.html |title=Adriana Lima, Forbes Top Celebrities |work=Forbes |accessdate=May 21, 2007}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2008, Lima was featured on the cover of ''Esquire'', re-creating the classic 1966 [[Angie Dickinson]] cover on Esquire's 75th anniversary. She appeared only in shoes, diamonds and gloves for the November 2007 issue of ''Vanity Fair'' celebrating 20 years of supermodels with her fellow Victoria's Secret Angels.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nothing to Hide|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/features/video/2007/victoriassecret_video200711|work=Vanity Fair|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081024061831/http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/features/video/2007/victoriassecret_video200711|archivedate=October 24, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref> In February 2008, she was chosen to be the face of Mexico's [[Liverpool (store)|Liverpool]] department store chain and launched the partnership with a press conference, runway show, and a summer campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wireimage.com/celebrity-pictures/Model-Adriana-Lima-arrives-to-Liverpool-Santa-Fe-to-attend-Fashion/80077473|title=Model Adriana Lima arrives to Liverpool Santa Fe to attend Fashion Fest 2008... 80077473|work=WireImage|date=February 29, 2008|accessdate=November 25, 2012}}</ref>\n\nLima returned to the high fashion runway in 2009, walking for [[Givenchy]]. In the same year, after visiting Turkey, she signed a contract with [[Doritos]] to appear in print campaigns and television commercials which began airing in Turkey that April. She was also one of the faces of Givenchy for the Fall/Winter 2009 season.\n\nIn 2011, Lima signed a deal as a spokeswoman for Megacity by Votsu, a Brazilian social gaming company, to appear in their commercials. Lima has worked with the most established photographers in fashion such as [[Annie Leibovitz]], [[Juergen Teller]], [[Bruce Weber (photographer)|Bruce Weber]], J.R. Duran, [[Paolo Roversi]], [[Inez van Lamsweerde|Inez van Lamsweerde and Vinoodh Matidin]], Vincent Peters, [[Mario Sorrenti]], [[Mert Alas and Marcus Piggott]], [[Steven Meisel]], [[David Sims (photographer)|David Sims]], and [[Mario Testino]].\n\nShe became the face of [[Donna Karan]]'s spring 2012 advertising campaign, which was accused of having racist undertones due to a photo featuring Lima posing in front of huddled local Haitians.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2011/12/15/adriana-lima-donna-karan-ads_n_1152124.html|title=Adriana Lima Donna Karan Ads For Spring 2012: Are They Misguided?|last=Misener|first=Jessica|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=December 15, 2011|accessdate=May 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn early 2012, Turkish clothing company [[Mavi Jeans]], contracted with Lima to be the face and spokesmodel for the brand. In the first quarter of 2012, her advertisement campaign increased sales by 50%. It also provided a 20% increase in stores and online traffic. Furthermore, her television commercial, which was watched by 28 million people, became a trending topic at Twitter and the number of people on Mavi's [[Facebook]] page increased by 20%. Store officials at Mavi say the clothing Lima wore in the ad campaigns was met with so much demand that they ran out of stock. Due to her success rate with the company, the European and Russian branch of Mavi decided to make her the global face of the brand.\n\nLima was photographed by artist Richard Phillips on the famed Copacabana sidewalk in Brazil for Visionaire no. 62 which was released in mid-2012.\n\nIn an interview, Phillips talks about Lima: \"She's so powerful, really an entity, in a way.\" Then added \"You meet her and there's a generosity of spirit and very friendly and easy manner, and then all of sudden, the lights go on, and you realize you're working with this absolutely extraordinary person who's capable of creating these powerful images.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/thecut/2012/09/first-looks-richard-phillips-on-adriana-lima.html |title=First Looks: Artist Richard Phillips Talks Adriana Lima and Lindsay Lohan - The Cut |work=New York Magazine |date=September 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\nFor the second time, she was featured in the Pirelli calendar by setting a record of being the first pregnant woman to be ever featured in the calendar for the 2013 edition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/pirelli-calendar-2013-adriana-lima-pregnant-models-not-nude-first-time-years-photos-905858|title=Pirelli Calendar 2013: Adriana Lima Pregnant, Models Not Nude For The First Time In Years [PHOTOS]|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=November 28, 2012|accessdate=July 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2013, Spanish fashion brand [[Desigual]] announced that Lima would be the face of the brand during Barcelona Fashion Week Spring-Summer '14,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.desigual.com/en/adriana-lima-para-desigual-en-el-080-barcelona-fashion/|title=Desigual blog: Adriana Lima for Desigual in the 080 Barcelona Fashion|publisher=Blog.Desigual.com|accessdate=July 8, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150425210633/http://blog.desigual.com/en/adriana-lima-para-desigual-en-el-080-barcelona-fashion/|archivedate=April 25, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> following [[Bar Refaeli]] in the same role on January 2013. In April 2014, Lima was chosen as the first brand ambassador of Desigual for the brand's 30th anniversary. She has been named the \"ambassador of la vida es Chula\", Desigual's \"life is cool\" motto. Desigual marketing director, Borja Castresana, stated that Adriana \"reflects our values and represents Desigual women who are confident, optimistic and full of life.\" The campaign was launched on 20 April 2014, with television commercials in Spain, France, Germany, Italy, Austria and Belgium.\n\nIn 2013, she ranked as the third highest paid supermodel according to [[Forbes]], with earnings of $6 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/vannale/2013/08/19/the-worlds-highest-paid-models-of-2013/2/|title=The World's Highest Paid Models 2013|last=Le|first=Vanna|work=[[Forbes]]|date=August 19, 2013|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref> In 2014, she ranked as the world's second highest paid supermodel with earnings of $8 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2014/08/18/the-worlds-highest-paid-models-of-2014-gisele-doutzen-and-adriana-steal-the-show/|title=The World's Highest-Paid Models Of 2014: Gisele, Doutzen And Adriana Steal The Show|last=Robehmed|first=Natalie|work=Forbes|date=August 18, 2014|accessdate=August 26, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2014, she returned to her role as a Maybelline New York spokesmodel. She had been the face of the brand between 2003 and 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/adriana-lima-returns-as-maybelline-new-york-spokesmodel|title=Adriana For Maybelline, Again|last=Niven-Phillips|first=Lisa|work=Vogue|date=June 19, 2014|accessdate=November 21, 2019}}</ref> Lima was also chosen as the new face of [[Jason Wu]] Fall/Winter 2014 campaign. Jason Wu stated about Lima, \"She's sexy, and there's this feline-esque prowess that felt appropriate for the clothes. And she's got those eyes! She's like our own [[Bianca Jagger]]. Adriana is a new take on the supermodel - she's from a different era. At the end of the day, these ads are about the women and the sexiness, and I continue to choose women who inspire me.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.ie/style/fashion/fashion-news/adriana-lima-is-the-new-face-of-jason-wu-30383844.html|title=Adriana Lima is the new face of Jason Wu|work=Independent.ie|date=June 25, 2014|accessdate=January 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2014, Lima starred in a campaign for luxury Swiss watch label [[International Watch Company|IWC]] alongside [[Karolina Kurkova]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/adriana-lima-karolina-kurkova-pose-iwc-watches-campaign-peter-lindbergh/|title=Adriana Lima & Karolina Kurkova Pose for IWC Watches Campaign by Peter Lindbergh|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=September 29, 2014|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, she became the face of [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue Eyewear]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popsugar.com/latina/Adriana-Lima-Modeling-Glasses-Vogue-Eyewear-38559458|title=Adriana Lima Modeling Glasses For Vogue Eyewear|work=PopSugar.com|date=October 5, 2015|accessdate=August 20, 2017}}</ref> and of [[Marc Jacobs]]' fragrance ''Decadence''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/designers/news/a10773/adriana-lima-marc-jacobs/|title=Adriana Lima is the Face of Marc Jacobs' New Fragance and His Met Gala Date|last=Kosin|first=Julie|work=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|date=May 4, 2015|accessdate=March 22, 2018}}</ref> In the same year, she was ranked as the world's second highest paid supermodel with earnings of $9 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/fashion/people/forbes-worlds-highest-paid-models-list/|title=Forbes World's Highest Paid Models list, all the latest styles|last=Sowray|first=Bibby|work=[[The Sunday Telegraph]]|date=September 17, 2015|accessdate=July 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2016, Lima became the face of Italian lingerie brand [[Calzedonia]]'s Swimwear collection.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.femalefirst.co.uk/lifestyle-fashion/stylenews/adriana-lima-new-face-calzedonia-937131.html|title=Adriana Lima Is New Face of Calzedonia|publisher=FemaleFirst|date=April 11, 2016|accessdate=January 21, 2017}}</ref> In July 2016, Lima was chosen by [[NBC]] alongside fellow Brazilian model [[Alessandra Ambrosio]] as the channel's food and culture correspondents for the [[2016 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/sports/adriana-lima-and-alessandra-ambrosio-will-be-contributors-at-2016-rio-olympics/|title=Alessandra Ambrosio and Adriana Lima Will Be Olympic Cultural Contributors: 'Sports Run in Our Blood!'|last=Minutaglio|first=Ross|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=July 19, 2016|accessdate=January 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nbcsportsgrouppressbox.com/2016/07/19/brazilian-supermodels-alessandra-ambrosio-and-adriana-lima-join-nbc-olympics-coverage-in-rio/|title=Brazilian supermodels Alessandra Ambrosio and Adriana Lima join NBC Olympics' coverage in Rio|website=NBC Sports Pressbox|date=July 19, 2016|accessdate=January 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, Lima starred in the ready-to-wear Spring/Summer 2017 campaign for the Italian brand [[Sportmax]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/adriana-lima-sportmax-spring-2017-campaign/|title=ADRIANA LIMA TAKES A DIP IN SPORTMAX'S SPRING 2017 ADS|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=January 28, 2017|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Lima became a brand ambassador for [[Puma (brand)|Puma]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.fashionnetwork.com/news/Adriana-Lima-is-Puma-s-latest-brand-ambassador,1020148.html|title=Adriana Lima is Puma's latest brand ambassador|work=Fashion Network|date=October 2, 2018|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> and for the Brazilian-based footwear and accessories label Schutz.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/adriana-lima-schutz-campaign/|title=Adriana Lima Poses Around NYC in Schutz' Summer 2018 Campaign|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=May 21, 2018|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Lima was the face of Miu Miu cruise campaign,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/kendall-jenner-miu-miu-cruise-2019-campaign/|title=Kendall Jenner Gets Luxe in Miu Miu Cruise 2019 Campaign|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=November 6, 2018|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> of [[Chopard]] Spring/Summer campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/work/chopard-chopard-with-adriana-lima|title=Chopard with Adriana Lima Spring 2019|work=Models.com|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> She was also the face of the Maybelline x Puma collaboration,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/adriana-lima-puma-maybelline-makeup/|title=Adriana Lima PUMA x Maybelline Campaign|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=January 21, 2019|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> of the Schutz resort 2019 campaign,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashiongonerogue.com/adriana-lima-schutz-resort-19-campaign/|title=Adriana Lima Flaunts Her Legs in Schutz Resort '19 Campaign|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=March 15, 2019|accessdate=April 14, 2019}}</ref> and starred in the [[Palms Casino Resort]] commercial with others including [[Cardi B]] and [[Rita Ora]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://us.hola.com/celebrities/2019032822459/cardib-palm-casino-vegas/|title=Mic drop! Watch Cardi B, Ozuna and Adriana Lima's $690 million Las Vegas launch|work=Hola!|date=March 28, 2019|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Victoria's Secret===\n[[File:Adriana-Lima FantaysBra-Chgo 2010-12-10 photoby-Bielawski.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Adriana Lima with the 2010 Fantasy Bra]]\nLima is probably best known for her work with [[Victoria's Secret]]. She walked her first Victoria's Secret runway in 1999,<ref name=\"People\"/> at age 17<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/adriana-limas-9-favorite-victorias-secret-fashion-show-looks-photos|title=Adriana Lima's 9 Favorite Victoria's Secret Fashion Show Looks (Photos)|last=Cunningham|first=Erin|work=[[The Daily Beast]]|date=December 9, 2013|accessdate=January 31, 2019}}</ref> and since being contracted as an Angel in 2000, she has appeared on subsequent shows ever since, opening the show in 2003, 2007, 2008, and 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/adriana-lima-victorias-secrets-angel-and-her-style-evolution-2001-2011-photos-553452|title=Adriana Lima: Victoria's Secret's Angel and Her Style Evolution from 2001 to 2011 [PHOTOS]|work=International Business Times|date=December 2, 2011|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref> In 2012, she opened the show for the 5th time less than two months after giving birth to her second child.<ref>{{cite wb|url=https://www.today.com/style/adriana-lima-walks-catwalk-two-months-after-giving-birth-flna1C6955809|title= Adriana Lima walks the catwalk \u2014 two months after giving birth|work=Today.com|date=November 8, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2012/11/08/adriana-lima-wows-at-victoria-secret-show-two-months-after-giving-birth/|title=Adriana Lima Wows at Victoria's Secret Show Two Months After Giving Birth|work=Fox News Latino|date=November 8, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121112143222/http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2012/11/08/adriana-lima-wows-at-victoria-secret-show-two-months-after-giving-birth/|archivedate=November 12, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, she was one of the five Angels promoting Victoria's Secret nationwide in the so-called \"Angels Across America\" Tour, alongside [[Tyra Banks]], [[Heidi Klum]], [[Gisele B\u00fcndchen]] and [[Alessandra Ambrosio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zimbio.com/Victoria%27s+Secret+Fashion+Show+2004/articles/b5fCp4A1U_D/Victoria+Secret+Fashion+Show+2004+Angels+Across|title=Victoria's Secret Fashion Show 2004: Angels Across America (Pictures)|work=Zimbio|date=May 20, 2011}}</ref> She missed the 2009 show due to her pregnancy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/adriana-lima-victoria-secret-fashion-192711696.html|title=Adriana Lima's Victoria's Secret Fashion Show Looks Through the Years|work=YaHoo!|date=December 5, 2016}}</ref> Lima has appeared on several television ads for the brand, including the praised and criticized \"Angel in Venice\" commercial of 2003 with [[Bob Dylan]].<ref name=\"usatoday1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/people/2004-04-05-bob-dylan_x.htm|title=Dylan appearing in Victoria's Secret ad|last=Cox|first=Dean|work=[[USA Today]]|date=April 5, 2004|accessdate=September 19, 2007}}</ref>\n\n2008 continued with Lima hosting the ''What Is Sexy?'' program for the E! Entertainment Network and a July tour for the BioFit Uplift Bra launch. She was also featured in November's Miracle Bra relaunch. Topping the year off, Lima wore the \"[[Victoria's Secret Fashion Show#Fantasy Bra|Fantasy Bra]]\" for the 2008 Victoria's Secret Fashion Show. The bra, created by American jewelry designer [[Martin Katz (American jewelry designer)|Martin Katz]], was set with 3,575 black diamonds, 117 certified {{convert|1|carat|mg}} white round diamonds, 34 rubies, and two black diamond drops totaling {{convert|100|carat|g}}. Valued at over $5 million, the bra carried more than {{convert|1500|carat|g}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationaljewelernetwork.com/njn/content_display/fashion/jewelry-fashion-reports/e3i0731a97427122625bd86e624cbcff394|title=Victoria's Secret unveils 2008 'Fantasy Bra|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100114112343/http://www.nationaljewelernetwork.com/njn/content_display/fashion/jewelry-fashion-reports/e3i0731a97427122625bd86e624cbcff394|archivedate=January 14, 2010|work=[[Jewelers of America#National Jeweler|National Jeweler]]|date=October 20, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, she again wore the Fantasy Bra, called the Victoria's Secret Bombshell Fantasy Bra. The bra which weighs in at 142 carats with 60 carats of white diamonds and 82 carats of topazes and sapphires is worth 2 million dollars.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2010/10/20/exclusive-adriana-lima-in-2-million-dollar-victorias-secret-bombshell-fantasy-bra/|title=EXCLUSIVE: Watch Adriana Lima Show Off Victoria's Secret $2 Million Bra|work=People|date=February 10, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314175906/http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2010/10/20/exclusive-adriana-lima-in-2-million-dollar-victorias-secret-bombshell-fantasy-bra/|archivedate=March 14, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> She wore the fantasy bra again in 2014, along with Alessandra Ambrosio, with each bra valuing $2,000,000.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://people.com/style/victorias-secret-fantasy-bras-yep-there-are-two-for-2014-get-the-first-look-and-exclusive-photos/ |title=Victoria's Secret Fantasy Bras (Yep, There are Two!) for 2014: Get the First Look and Exclusive Photos! |date=November 1, 2014 |website=People}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2016, Victoria's Secret launched its own sports bra line, ''Victoria Sport'', and Lima starred on the commercial alongside models [[Elsa Hosk]], [[Romee Strijd]], [[Jasmine Tookes]] and [[Josephine Skriver]].<ref>{{YouTube|-1jTNlOPG6Q|Introducing Victoria Sport}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/victorias-secret-sport-photoshoot/|title=Adriana Lima & More Angels Work Up a Sweat in Victoria Sport|work=Fashion Rogue|date=November 6, 2016|accessdate=May 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, Lima was named \"the most valuable Victoria's Secret Angel\" according to analytics company D'Marie,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whowhatwear.com/most-valuable-victorias-secret-model/slide5|title=This Is Officially the Most Valuable Victoria's Secret Angel|work=Who What Wear|date=January 2, 2017|accessdate=January 17, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118053351/http://www.whowhatwear.com/most-valuable-victorias-secret-model/slide5|archivedate=January 18, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> which conducted research that factored in social media likes, followers, sales conversions and engagement to come up with the results. \"We've developed an algorithm that compiles over 24 specific metrics from each social media platform that determines an individual's ranking amongst others' in any variety of categories,\" D'Marie explained.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/life-style/fashion/88173889/adriana-lima-named-most-valuable-victorias-secret-angel|title=Adriana Lima named most valuable Victoria's Secret Angel|work=[[Stuff.co.nz]]|date=January 6, 2017|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2018, Lima walked in her final Victoria's Secret Fashion Show after participating in 20 catwalks for the brand.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/adriana-lima-final-victorias-secret-fashion-show-2018|title=See Adriana Lima's Emotional Final Walk for Victoria's Secret|last=Okwodu|first=Janelle|work=Vogue|date=November 8, 2018|accessdate=November 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Acting and hosting===\nLima's made her acting debut alongside [[Mickey Rourke]] and [[Forest Whitaker]], in ''[[The Hire#The Follow|The Follow]]'' (2001), a short film in [[BMW]]'s series ''[[The Hire]]'', opposite [[Clive Owen]] and directed by [[Wong Kar-wai]]. She also appeared with her fellow Angels in a guest spot playing herself in the [[CBS]] comedy series ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]'' in November 2007, in the episode \"[[The Yips (How I Met Your Mother)|The Yips]]\". She also played herself, along with fellow Victoria's Secret Angels, in the 2013 series ''[[The Crazy Ones]]'' alongside [[Robin Williams]] and [[Sarah Michelle Gellar]]. In 2008, Lima appeared on the American television series ''[[Ugly Betty]]'', where she played herself and made friends with the series' title character, [[Betty Suarez]].\n\nLima was the host and executive producer of the American reality competition show ''American Beauty Stars'', which premiered on September 23, 2017 on [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2017/09/20/supermodel-adriana-lima-takes-us-set-lifetimes-american-beauty-star/664689001/|title=Supermodel Adriana Lima takes us on the set of Lifetime's 'American Beauty Star'|last=Mallenbaum|first=Carly|work=[[USA Today]]|date=September 20, 2017|accessdate=September 24, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Lima made a cameo appearance as herself in the film ''[[Ocean's 8]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/oceans-8-cameos-saul-yen-matt-damon/2/ |title=Ocean's 8: ALL of the Cameos You Missed |date=June 9, 2018 |website=Screen Rant}}</ref>\n\n===Super Bowl ads===\nLima's 2008 solo Victoria's Secret's [[Super Bowl XLII]] ad was the single most-seen ad of the game, watched by 103.7 million viewers.<ref name=\"usatoday2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/money/advertising/2008-02-07-super-bowl-ads_N.htm |title=Close Super Bowl puts even more eyes on late-airing ads|work=USA Today|date=July 2, 2008}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2012, Lima became the only celebrity to ever star in two Super Bowl commercials in one game. She starred in [[Super Bowl XLVI]] commercials for online flower service [[Teleflora]] and [[Kia Motors]] which were watched by more than 200 million viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/entertainmentnewsbuzz/2012/02/super-bowl-ads-teleflora-taps-model-adriana-lima.html|title=Super Bowl ads: Super model Adriana Lima in demand |work=Los Angeles Times|date=February 3, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/fash-track/adriana-lima-super-bowl-commercials-gisele-bundchen-287276|title=Model Adriana Lima Stars in Two Super Hot Super Bowl Commercials|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 6, 2012}}</ref> Her Kia Motors Super Bowl commercial \u2013 promoting the new Kia Optima \u2013 sent sales to their highest mark since the design debuted. Sales were up 31% from January 2012 and 138.6% from February 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/kicking-tires/post/did-super-bowl-xlvi-ads-impact-car-sales/2012/03/02/gIQAtUllmR_blog.html|title=Did Super Bowl XLVI Ads Impact Car Sales|author=Cars.com|work=The Washington Post|date=March 2, 2012|accessdate=July 7, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.suntimes.com/news/steinberg/13178798-452/obama-needs-a-brazilian-supermodel.html|title=Obama needs a Brazilian supermodel|work=Chicago Sun-Times|accessdate=July 7, 2012}}</ref> The commercial was also voted No.3 out of the 55 commercials on USA TODAY and Facebook's Super Bowl Ad Meter.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/superbowl46/admeter.htm |title=2012 USA TODAY Facebook Super Bowl Ad Meter: Rate the ads |work=USA Today |date=February 5, 2012 |accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/money/advertising/story/2012-02-07/usa-today-facebook-super-bowl-ad-meter-final-scores/53004026/1|title=USA TODAY Facebook Super Bowl Ad Meter Scores|date=February 8, 2012|work=USA Today|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120415220228/https://www.usatoday.com/money/advertising/story/2012-02-07/usa-today-facebook-super-bowl-ad-meter-final-scores/53004026/1|archivedate=April 15, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> A teaser of the commercial was released in movie theaters in January before the game. It is believed to be the first time a Super Bowl commercial premiered in movie theaters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/entertainmentnewsbuzz/2012/01/kia-motors-usa-to-premiere-super-bowl-ad-in-theaters.html|title=Kia Motors USA to premiere Super Bowl ad in theaters|work=Los Angeles Times|date=January 20, 2012|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref>\n\nForbes named her Teleflora commercial as one of the best during Super Bowl XLVI, with the comment, \"Teleflora ... Adriana Lima. 'Nuff said\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/prishe/2012/02/06/the-winners-and-losers-of-super-bowl-commercials-in-2012/|title=The Winners and Losers of Super Bowl Commercials in 2012|last=Rishe|first=Patrick|work=Forbes|date=April 18, 2012|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref> Among the many reviews of the commercial, The Huffington Post said: \"One of the basic goals of any commercial is to capture the viewer's attention, and by this measure, Teleflora.com's ad featuring supermodel Adriana Lima was most definitely successful.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/02/06/super-bowl-commercials-2012-adriana-lima-video_n_1255185.html|title=Adriana Lima Teleflora.Com Super Bowl Commercial: Sexy Ad Stirs Controversy (VIDEO)|last=Greenberg|first=Chris|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=February 6, 2012|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref> ESPN.com noted: \"This actually makes sense when you think about it: Launch your Valentine's Day campaign in the middle of the Super Bowl. That's actually what flower company Teleflora is doing on Sunday. Even smarter? Hire supermodel Adriana Lima to star in it.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/espn/page2/story/_/id/7527035/from-bark-side-bueller-look-2012-super-bowl-commercials|title=Many Super Bowl commercials are out|last=Carter|first=Kelley|work=[[ESPN]]|date=February 1, 2012|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nFrom 2001 to 2003, Lima was in a relationship with American singer [[Lenny Kravitz]].<ref name=\"ISTO\u00c9\"/> They moved in together and got engaged.<ref name=\"ISTO\u00c9\"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/lenny-kravitz-the-star-is-born-again-231577/ |title=Lenny Kravitz: The Star Is Born Again |last=Edwards |first=Gavin |date=June 24, 2004 |website=Rolling Stone}}</ref> Lima was featured on the music video for Kravitz's 2002 single, \"[[Lenny (album)|Yesterday Is Gone (My Dear Kay)]]\".<ref name=\"yesterday\">{{YouTube|id=1zGJZSvuBfI|title=Lenny Kravitz - Yesterday Is Gone (My Dear Kay)}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Lima married Serbian [[National Basketball Association|NBA]] player [[Marko Jari\u0107]] on [[Valentine's Day]] in [[Jackson Hole, Wyoming]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2009/02/adriana_lima_got_married.html|title=Adriana Lima Got Married|last=Odell|first=Amy|work=[[New York Magazine]]|date=February 24, 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"people1\">{{cite web|last=Wihlborg|first=Ulrica |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20261007,00.html|title=Supermodel Adriana Lima Elopes!|work=People|date=February 23, 2009}}</ref> In May 2009, it was reported that Lima had applied for Serbian citizenship,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rts.rs/page/stories/sr/story/15/Zanimljivosti/64169/Ne+srpska+snajka%2C+ve%C4%87+snajka+Srpkinja.html |title=Adrijana Lima \u017eeli dr\u017eavljanstvo Srbije|work=Radio-televizjia Srbije|language=Serbian|date=May 27, 2009}}</ref> but it was never granted to her.<ref name=\"Alo-not-citizen\">{{cite web|url=http://www.alo.rs/v-i-p/svetski-dzet-set/adrijana-lima-nikada-nije-uzela-srpski-pasos/54368|title=Adrijana Lima nikada nije uzela srpski paso\u0161!|trans-title=Adriana Lima Never Took Serbian Passport!|publisher=[[Alo (newspaper)|Alo]]|date=May 8, 2014|accessdate=April 1, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701163330/http://www.alo.rs/v-i-p/svetski-dzet-set/adrijana-lima-nikada-nije-uzela-srpski-pasos/54368|archivedate=July 1, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Jari\u0107 and Lima have two daughters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-moms/news/adriana-lima-gives-birth-to-daughter-sienna-2012129/|title=Adriana Lima Gives Birth to Daughter Sienna! |work=UsMagazine.com|date=September 12, 2012}}</ref> On May 2, 2014, Lima and Jari\u0107 announced their separation after five years of marriage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/adriana-lima-husband-marko-jaric-split-supermodel-announces-divorce-201425/|title=Adriana Lima Splits From Husband Marko Jaric After 5 Years of Marriage: Supermodel Announces Separation From Former NBA Player|last=Lee|first=Esther|work=[[Us Weekly]]|date=May 2, 2014|accessdate=August 13, 2018}}</ref> The divorce was finalized in March 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pagesix.com/2016/03/15/adriana-lima-and-marko-jaric-finalize-divorce/|title=Adriana Lima is divorced|last=Johnson|first=Richard|work=Page Six|date=March 15, 2015|accessdate=September 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Religious views===\nLima is a devout Roman Catholic who attends [[Mass (Catholic Church)|Mass]] every Sunday. In April 2006, she told ''GQ'' that she was a [[Virginity|virgin]]. \"Sex is for after marriage,\" she said. \"[Men] have to respect that this is my choice. If there's no respect, that means they don't want me.\" She also denounced [[abortion]] as a crime, and stated that she agrees with all of the Church's teachings.<ref name=gq>{{cite magazine|first=Lisa|last=DePaulo|url=https://www.gq.com/women/photos/200603/adriana-lima-virgin-underwear-model|title=Adriana Lima: Our favorite ... virgin?|magazine=[[GQ]]|location=New York City|date=April 2006}}</ref><ref name=\"plan\">{{cite web|url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0506/17/sbt.01.html|title=Tom Cruise Proposes to Katie Holmes; Angelina Jolie's Personal Life Full of Drama; Picks and Pans of New Movies|work=[[Showbiz Tonight]]|date=June 17, 2005}}</ref> Lima is known to bring a [[Bible]] with her backstage before she goes onstage. She has also stated that, before she became a [[Victoria's Secret Angel]], she had wanted to become a [[nun]]. Regarding her spirituality, Lima stated, \"The church is in me \u2014 I always connect. If you're connected with the divine and always have pure intentions with everything you're doing, you're protected by the angels. I'm very spiritual. I believe in nature, I believe in energy, I believe in spirits.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/victorias-secret-angel-adriana-lima-the-church-is-in-me|title=Adriana Lima wanted to be a nun|work=[[Fox News]]|date=February 27, 2017|accessdate=August 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Charity work===\nLima does charitable work helping with an [[orphanage]], \"Caminhos da Luz\" (Paths of Light), located in Salvador. She helps with construction to expand the orphanage and buys clothes for poor children in Salvador, Bahia.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pirelli.com/tyre/br/pt/news/2012/10/01/calendario-pirelli-2013-por-steve-mccurry/ |title=Calend\u00e1rio Pirelli 2013 por Steve McCurry |date=October 1, 2012 |website=Pirelli.com |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref name=\"caminhosdaluz\">[https://archive.today/20130104205852/http://www.superiorpics.com/adriana_lima/interview.html Adriana helping her charity]. Superiorpics.com. Retrieved 2011-08-10.</ref> In 2009, she appeared on ''[[Var m\u0131s\u0131n? Yok musun?]]'', the Turkish version of ''[[Deal or No Deal]]'', where her prize money went to a hospital in [[Istanbul]] for children fighting leukemia.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/cadde/galeri/var-misin-yok-musunda-adriana-ruzgari-1051661/1 |title=Var m\u0131s\u0131n yok musun'da Adriana r\u00fczgar\u0131 |date=January 26, 2009 |website=milliyet.com |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IqsGi1a0VT8 |title=BESIKTAS'LI ADRIANA LIMA WINS 75,000$ on Deal or No Deal |date=January 26, 2009 |website=YouTube}}</ref>\n\n==Public image==\nLima was listed in the 2005 Forbes' edition of The World's Best-Paid Celebrities Under 25.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://moneycentral.msn.com/content/invest/forbes/P140854.asp|title=Forbes: The World's Best-Paid Celebrities Under 25 |work=MSN |date=January 11, 2006|accessdate=October 10, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090125213125/http://moneycentral.msn.com/content/invest/forbes/P140854.asp|archive-date=January 25, 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref> She ranked ninety-nine in the 2005 and 2006 Forbes' edition of The [[Celebrity 100]] lists.<ref>{{cite web|author=Lea Goldman & Kiri Blakely|url=https://www.forbes.com/2006/06/12/06celebrities_money-power-celebrities-list_land.html|title=The Celebrity 100 |work=Forbes|date=June 15, 2006}}</ref> In 2012, she was listed in Forbes Celebrity 100 power list for earning more than 7 million between May 2011 and May 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hannahelliott/2012/05/16/on-the-celebrity-100-gisele-tops-kate/|title=On The Celebrity 100, Gisele Tops Kate|first=Hannah|last=Elliott|publisher=|accessdate=July 28, 2016}}</ref> In 2012, she ranked number eight in forbes' \"The World's Most Powerful Latino Celebrities\" list for earning more than 7 million dollars.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2012/05/25/the-worlds-most-powerful-latino-celebrities/2/ |title=The World's Most Powerful Latino Celebraties|work=Forbes|date=May 25, 2012}}</ref>\n\nLima was chosen to be a part of ''People'' magazine's 100 most beautiful people in the world list, sharing that space with the Angels, with whom she also received a star on the Hollywood \"Walk of Fame\" prior to the 2007 Victoria's Secret Fashion Show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.starpulse.com/Supermodels/Lima,_Adriana/Videos/?vxChannel=&vxClipId=&clip_id=9juVYym30l9QrCE1&video_title=USA%3A+Victoria's+Secret%22angels%22honored+with+a+star+on+the+Hollywood+walk+of+fame |title=USA: Victoria's Secret\"angels\"honored with a star on the Hollywood walk of fame Video - Adriana Lima Videos |publisher=Starpulse.com |accessdate=2012-10-25}}</ref> That same year, she ranked 7th on ''[[FHM]]''s \"[[FHM's 100 Sexiest Women (UK)|100 Sexiest Women 2007]]\" list.<ref name=\"fhm\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fhmonline.com/girls_100_sexiest_2007.asp?cnl_id=1&stn_id=136&p=48|title=No.7 Adriana Lima and No.6 Jessica Biel \u2013 100 Sexiest Women 2007|work=[[FHM]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070606103259/http://www.fhmonline.com/girls_100_sexiest_2007.asp?cnl_id=1&stn_id=136&p=48 |archivedate=June 6, 2007}}</ref>\n\nLima was also voted on ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]''{{'}}s \"Hot 100\" 2007 at the No. 53 spot. She was voted No.1 as the Most Desirable Woman in 2005 by visitors of the men's lifestyle website [[AskMen]].com and placed 4th in 2006 and 2007, 10th in 2008, and 19th in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ca.askmen.com/media_kit/press_release/press_release_a14.html |title=AskMen.com - Press Releases |publisher=AskMen |date=January 31, 2008 |accessdate=October 25, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113113237/http://ca.askmen.com/media_kit/press_release/press_release_a14.html |archivedate=November 13, 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.askmen.com/media_kit/press_release/press_release_a11.html |title=Press Releases |publisher=AskMen.com |accessdate=October 25, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113113237/http://www.askmen.com/media_kit/press_release/press_release_a11.html |archivedate=November 13, 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref> She received the award for \"Hottest Girl on the Planet\" in the 2007 [[Spike Guys' Choice Awards]].<ref>[[Spike Guys' Choice Awards]]</ref> Since November 2008, Models.com has featured her at number one on the list of the \"Sexiest Models\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/rankings/sexiest/list.html?model_id=1545#1545|title=No.1 Sexiest model|work= Models.com|accessdate=October 8, 2011}}</ref> In July 2011, she was ranked No. 4 in the website's \"Money Girls\" list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/rankings/money/list.html?model_id=1545#1545 |title=Money Girls List|work=Models.com}}</ref> The website also lists her on \"the Supers\" list. The list, which has only 8 [[supermodels]], is about supermodels that transcend the boundaries of the fashion industry and have public recognition in and out of fashion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/rankings/ui/TheSupers|title=MODELS.com's The Supers|work=Models.com}}</ref> In 2010, she was voted eighth in \"[[FHM's 100 Sexiest Women (UK)|FHM's Sexiest Women in the World]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/100-sexiest-2009/adriana-lima/|title=FHM Ranking - 100 Sexiest of 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090715231033/http://www.fhm.com/100-sexiest-2009/adriana-lima/|work=FHM.com|archivedate=July 15, 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref> FHM ranked her at No. 6 in 2009, No. 21 in 2008 and No. 4 in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/adriana-lima|title=Adriana Lima|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110109195042/http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/adriana-lima|archivedate=January 9, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Lima was ranked No. 46 on the 50 most popular women on the Web according to Google search results.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Technology/50-popular-women-web-google-search-results/story?id=10573331|title=50 Most Popular Women on the Web, Per Google Search Results|work=ABC News|date=May 6, 2010}} April 15, 2010, COED Magavine.</ref> A results from a market research study in 2011 about the [[UEFA Champions League]] released by [[Heineken]], showed that 52% of men would rather watch their team lift the Champions League trophy than go on a date with Lima.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2011/05/23/1670831/0/en/Men-Give-Up-Supermodels-for-Champions-League-Final.html |title=Men Give Up Supermodels for Champions League Final |date=May 23, 2011 |website=GlobeNewsWire}}</ref> [[McAfee]] ranked Lima as the 6th most \"dangerous\" celebrity in cyberspace in 2010. The ranking, relating to the use of the names of popular celebrities to lure people to websites that are laden with [[malicious software]], ranked Lima number eight in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://home.mcafee.com/advicecenter/most-dangerous-celebrities?ctst=1|title=Heidi Klum Named Most Dangerous Celebrity in Cyberspace|work=mcafee.com|date=September 15, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111217121808/http://home.mcafee.com/advicecenter/most-dangerous-celebrities?ctst=1|archivedate=December 17, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2012, [[Complex (magazine)|Complex]] ranked her 4th in the list of \"The 100 Hottest Supermodels of All Time\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2012/11/the-100-hottest-supermodels-of-all-time/#gallery|title=The 100 Hottest Supermodels of All Time|work=Complex|date=November 15, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn October 6, 2015, it was announced that Adriana will have her own wax figure at the [[Madame Tussauds New York]]. She is the first Victoria's Secret Angel and the second Brazilian figure to join the Tussauds star lineup, after soccer star [[Pel\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Wax figure of Adriana Lima added to Madame Tussauds New York|url=https://news.yahoo.com/wax-figure-adriana-lima-added-madame-tussauds-york-124207430.html|publisher=[[Yahoo]]|date=October 6, 2015}}</ref> Her wax figure was unveiled on 30 November 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/adriana-lima-madame-tussauds-wax-figure|title=Adriana Lima Is the Most Famous Victoria's Secret Angel|last=Okwodu|first=Janelle|work=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|date=November 30, 2015|accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, she was chosen as the Fashion Icon honoree at the Daily Front Row Awards.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://sg.style.yahoo.com/adriana-lima-honoured-daily-front-row-fashion-awards-010000314.html |title=Adriana Lima honoured at Daily Front Row Fashion Awards |date=March 17, 2019 |website=Yahoo!}}</ref>\n\n===Criticism===\nIn a 2011 interview with ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', prior to the Victoria's Secret Fashion Show, Lima said that for nine days before the show she drinks only [[protein shake]]s, and no liquids at all for the last 12 hours \"so you dry out, sometimes you can lose up to eight pounds just from that.\" She also stated that for the last three weeks before the show, she works out twice a day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/news-features/TMG8872623/Victorias-Secret-show-What-does-it-take-to-be-a-Victorias-Secret-Angel.html|title=Victoria's Secret show: What does it take to be a Victoria's Secret Angel?|last=Whitworth|first=Melissa|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=November 7, 2011|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref> The interview prompted criticism from the media commentators.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.styleite.com/media/anderson-cooper-adriana-lima-ridiculist/|title=Anderson Cooper &#124; Adriana Lima's Diet &#124; The Ridiculist|last=Fenner|first=Justin|work=Styleite|date=November 11, 2011|accessdate=December 25, 2012}}</ref> Shortly afterwards, Lima defended herself in an interview with [[E!]]. \"I know it's very intense but ... I just have an athlete's mind and I appreciate doing this thing,\" she said. \"It's not that I do crazy diets throughout the year. I just do it for this particular thing. After this show, I become normal again.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/bodies/victorias-secret-fashion-show-adriana-lima-extreme-diet/|title=Victoria's Secret Fashion Show: Adriana Lima Extreme Diet|last=Hammel|first=Sara|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=November 11, 2011|accessdate=March 31, 2019}}</ref> The Adriana Lima diet became one of the top five most searched diets on the web in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://healthland.time.com/2012/12/12/the-most-popular-diets-of-2012-according-to-google/slide/adriana-lima-diet/|title=The Most Popular Diets Of 2012 (According To Google)|last=Sifferlin|first=Alexandra|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=December 12, 2012|accessdate=November 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''Pista Dupla''\n|\n| TV series\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[The Hire: The Follow]]''\n| The Wife\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"The Yips\"\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Ugly Betty]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Ugly Betty\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[The Crazy Ones]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Models Love Magic\"\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Ocean's 8]]''\n| Herself\n| Cameo\n|-\n|}\n\n==Music video==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Artist\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Yesterday Is Gone (My Dear Kay)]]''\n| [[Lenny Kravitz]]<ref name=\"yesterday\"/>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Adriana Lima}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb name|0992596|Adriana Lima}}\n* {{Models.com}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20151229222616/http://www.thefashionstyles.com/adriana-lima/ Adriana Lima] at Fashion Styles\n* [http://www.vogue.com/tag/model/adriana-lima Adriana Lima] at [[Vogue Magazine]]\n* {{Fashionmodel}}\n\n{{Victoria's Secret Angels}}\n{{1995\u20131999 Victoria's Secret Fashion Show models}}\n{{2000\u20132009 Victoria's Secret Fashion Show models}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lima, Adriana}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Brazilian actresses]]\n[[Category:Brazilian emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Brazilian female models]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of indigenous peoples descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Japanese descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Portuguese descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Swiss descent]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Salvador, Bahia]]\n[[Category:Victoria's Secret Angels]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-move-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{Short description|Brazilian model and actress}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name         = Adriana Lima\n| image        = Adriana Lima 2019 by Glenn Francis.jpg\n| caption      = Lima in July 2019\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1981|6|12}}\n| birth_place  = [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]], [[Bahia]], [[Brazil]]\n| occupation   = {{hlist|Model|actress}}\n| years_active = 1996\u2013present\n| height       = {{convert|1.78|m|ftin|abbr=on}}<ref name=\"fmd\">{{cite web|url=https://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/Adriana_Lima|title=Adriana Lima - Fashion Model|work=Fashion Model Directory|accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"models.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.models.com/models/Adriana-Lima|title=Adriana Lima - Model Profile - Photos & latest news|work=Models.com|accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n| haircolor    = Dark Brown<ref name=\"fmd\"/><ref name=\"models.com\"/>\n| eyecolor     = Blue<ref name=\"fmd\"/><ref name=\"models.com\"/>\n| spouse       = {{marriage|[[Marko Jari\u0107]]|2009|2016|reason=divorced}}\n| children     = 2\n| agency       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Creative Artists Agency]] (New York, Los Angeles)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/adriana-lima-signs-with-caa-1203234766/|title=Adriana Lima Signs With Creative Artists Agency|work=WWD|date=August 7, 2019|accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Elite Model Management]] (Paris, London, Milan)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.models.com/models/Adriana-Lima|title=Adriana Lima - Model|publisher=}}</ref>\n}}\n| website      = {{URL|http://www.adrianalima.com/|www.AdrianaLima.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Adriana Lima'''<ref name=\"Full name\">{{YouTube|lO4d-Mxvb3Q|W Radio Colombia Interview - Part 1}}</ref> ({{IPA-pt|ad\u027ei\u02c8\u00e3n\u0250 \u02c8lim\u0250|br}}; born June 12, 1981) is a Brazilian [[Model (person)|model]] and actress, best known as a [[Victoria's Secret Angel]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.victoriassecret.ca/vsallaccess/angels/adriana-lima|title=Adriana Lima - Victoria's Secret|work=[[Victoria's Secret]]|accessdate=January 17, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190117070150/https://www.victoriassecret.ca/vsallaccess/angels/adriana-lima|archivedate=January 17, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> from 1999 to 2018.<ref name=\"People\">{{cite web|url=https://people.com/style/victorias-secret-fashion-show-adriana-lima/|title=7 Reasons Adriana Lima Is the Guardian Angel of the Victoria's Secret Fashion Show|last=Talarico|first=Brittany|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=December 5, 2016|accessdate=October 1, 2018}}</ref> She was the longest-running model and named \"the most valuable Victoria's Secret Angel\" in 2017. She is also known as a spokesmodel for [[Maybelline]] cosmetics since 2003, and for her [[Super Bowl]] and [[Kia Motors]] commercials. At age 15, Lima won [[Ford Models|Ford]]'s \"Supermodel of Brazil\" competition, and took second place the following year in the Ford \"[[Supermodel of the World (contest)|Supermodel of the World]]\" competition before signing with [[Elite Model Management]] in [[New York City]].\n\nLima is currently ranked by models.com as one of the \"[[Supermodels|New Supers]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/rankings/ui/NewSupers/|title=The New Supers List|work=Models.com|accessdate=February 20, 2017}}</ref> Since 2014, Lima has been the world's second highest-paid model. In 2012, she came in 4th place on the ''[[Forbes]]'' top-earning models list, estimated to have earned $7.3 million in one year. In 2013, she came in 3rd place and in 2014 she came in 2nd place with earnings of $8 million. In 2015, she came in 2nd place with earnings of $9 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/briansolomon/2012/06/14/the-worlds-highest-paid-models/|title=The World's Highest Paid Models|last=Solomon|first=Brian|work=[[Forbes]]|date=June 14, 2012|accessdate=June 20, 2012}}</ref> In 2016, she kept the second place with earnings of {{US$|10.5 million|link=yes}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2016/08/30/the-worlds-highest-paid-models-2016-karlie-kloss-and-kendall-jenner-storm-top-three-with-10-million-apiece/|title=The World's Highest Paid Models 2016|last=Robehmed|first=Natalie|work=[[Forbes]]|date=August 30, 2016|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\nLima has served as brand ambassador for the clothing brand [[Desigual]] based in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]], for the Beachwear collection of Italian brand [[Calzedonia]], and for the ready-to-wear collection of Italian brand [[Sportmax]]. She is currently an ambassador for [[International Watch Company|IWC]], [[Puma (brand)|Puma]], and [[Chopard]].\n\n==Early life==\nLima was born on 12 June 1981 in [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador, Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instyle.com/celebrity/adriana-limas-birthday-serenade-will-give-you-goosebumps|title=Adriana Lima's Birthday Serenade Will Give You Goosebumps|last=Berg|first=Jenny|work=[[InStyle]]|date=June 13, 2017|accessdate=June 15, 2019}}</ref> Many sources stated that \"Francesca\" is her middle name, but Lima herself denied this in an interview to [[W Radio (Colombia)|W Radio Colombia]] in 2010, and confirmed that her name is only Adriana Lima.<ref name=\"Full name\"/> Her parents are Nelson Torres, a carpenter,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ego.globo.com/Gente/Noticias/0,,MUL327087-9798,00-ADRIANA+LIMA+DESCOBRE+QUE+O+PAI+FOI+SEU+IRMAO+EM+VIDA+PASSADA.html|title=Adriana Lima descobre que o pai foi seu irm\u00e3o em vida passada|last=Tecidio|first=Luciana|work=EGO.Globo.com|language=Portuguese|date=May 25, 2007}}</ref> and Maria das Gra\u00e7as Lima, a social worker.<ref name=\"ISTO\u00c9\">{{cite web|url=http://www.terra.com.br/istoegente/211/reportagens/capa_adriana_lima_02.htm|title=A princesa da moda|work=ISTO\u00c9 Gente|language=Portuguese|date=August 18, 2003|accessdate=November 24, 2016}}</ref> Her father left the family when she was six months old, and Lima was raised only by her mother.<ref name=\"ISTO\u00c9\"/>\n\nLima is of [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]], [[Swiss people|Swiss]], [[Native Brazilian]], [[Japanese people|Japanese]], [[African]] and [[West Indian]] descent<ref name=\"25things\">{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/lifestyle/fashion/25-things-you-may-not-know-about-victorias-secret-angel-adriana-lima/ss-BBjKo8E#image=22|title=25 things you may not know about Adriana Lima|work=MSN|date=May 14, 2015|accessdate=October 1, 2019}}</ref> (which classifies her as a [[Pardo Brazilians|Pardo Brazilian]]).<!-- Note: Do not remove this Brazilian demographic classification. -->{{efn|group=note|English translated sources and Lima herself states she has \"Indian\" ancestry. The ambiguous meaning of the word \"Indian\" in English, has led some to believe that the Amerindian \"indian\" ancestry originated from India, when in slang \"indian\" is meant to refer to indigenous peoples of the Americas. In Portuguese, such ambiguity is nonexistent, since there are two words to convey the different meanings: ''[[wikt:\u00edndio|\u00edndio]]'' for an [[Native Americans in the United States|American Indian]] (or [[Amerindian]], including Native Brazilians); and ''[[wikt:indiano#Portuguese|indiano]]'' for people and things related to India.}} But she considers herself [[Afro-Brazilian]].<ref>{{YouTube|id=k1sSbW61pdI|title=Adriana Lima talks about her mixed heritage}}</ref>\n\nLima speaks four languages: her native [[Brazilian Portuguese|Portuguese]], [[English language|English]], [[Italian language|Italian]], and [[Spanish language|Spanish]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vogue.it/en/encyclo/people/l/adriana-lima|title=Adriana Lima|publisher=Vogue Italy|accessdate=February 20, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151102024543/http://www.vogue.it/en/encyclo/people/l/adriana-lima|archivedate=November 2, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Adriana Lima by David Shankbone Cropped.JPG|left|thumb|upright|Lima at the premiere of ''[[Spider-Man 3]]'' at the [[Tribeca Film Festival]] in [[Queens]], [[New York City]] in 2007]]\nLima never thought about being a model, although she had won many beauty pageants in elementary school.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/adriana-lima-pictures_n_1582001|title=Adriana Lima's Style Evolution: From Brazilian Beauty Queen To Victoria's Secret Angel (PHOTOS)|last=Leon|first=Sarah|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=October 11, 2012|quote=Although today she is one of the highest-paid models in the world, Lima got her start competing in beauty pageants in her native Brazil.}}</ref> However, a friend at school who wanted to enter a modeling contest and did not want to enter alone, so Lima entered with her. Both sent in pictures, and the contest sponsor soon asked Lima to come out for the competition. Soon after, at age 15, she entered and finished in first place in Ford's \"Supermodel of Brazil\" model search. She subsequently entered the 1996 [[Ford Models Supermodel of the World]] contest and finished in second place.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.de/models/adriana-lima|title=Adriana Lima: Model-Portrait|publisher=Elle Germany|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref> Three years later, Lima moved to New York City and signed with [[Elite Model Management]].<ref name=\"Insider\">{{cite web|url=https://www.insider.com/adriana-limas-modeling-career-timeline-2018-11|title=Adriana Lima is hanging up her Victoria's Secret wings \u2014 here's a look back at her modeling career|last=Ngomsi|first=Vinciane|work=[[Insider Inc.]]|date=November 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHer first magazine cover was [[Marie Claire|Marie Claire Brazil]] in September 1998. Her first [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] covers were the Italian ''Vogue Gioiello'' in September 2000, on their 20th Anniversary issue, and Vogue Brasil the next month.<ref name=\"Insider\"/>\n\nAs a runway model, she has walked the catwalk for designers such as Rosa Cha, Blue man, Fashion's Night Out, Caio Gobbi, Fause Haten, M. Officer, Luca Luca, Liverpool Fashion, Dosso Dossi, Carmen Steffens, C\u00eda Maritima, Agua de Coco, Lino Villaventura, Forum, Vassarette, Zoomp, Joan Vass, Cori, [[Emilio Pucci]], [[Fendi]], [[Giles Deacon]], [[Carmen Marc Valvo]], [[Emanuel Ungaro]], [[Baby Phat]], [[Giorgio Armani]], [[Pierre Balmain|Balmain]], [[Bottega Veneta]], [[Sportmax]], [[Vera Wang]], [[Valentino Garavani|Valentino]], [[Miu Miu]], [[Givenchy]], [[Versace]], [[Cividini]], [[Alexandre Herchcovitch]], [[Jason Wu]], [[Marc Jacobs]], [[Christian Dior]], [[Paco Rabanne]], [[Victoria's Secret]], [[Sean John]], [[Prada]], [[Louis Vuitton]], [[Desigual]], [[Cynthia Rowley]], [[Sully Bonnelly]], [[Anna Sui]], [[Guy Laroche]], [[John Galliano]], [[Alexander McQueen]], [[Yigal Azrou\u00ebl]], [[Ralph Lauren]], [[Christian Lacroix]], [[Escada]], [[Nanette Lepore]], [[Richard Tyler (designer)|Richard Tyler]], [[Triton (fashion)|Triton]], and [[Betsey Johnson]].\n\nLima became a [[Guess (clothing)|GUESS?]] girl in 2000, appearing in that year's fall ad campaign. She also appeared in the book ''A Second Decade of Guess? Images''.<ref name=\"Insider\"/>\n\nLima continued to build upon her portfolio, doing more print work for [[Maybelline]], for whom she has worked as a spokesmodel since 2003 to 2009; Also in the same year, she appeared in the company's first calendar and did an ad campaign for [[Swatch]]. Lima has also worked for notable fashion brands [[Bebe Stores|bebe]], [[Armani]], [[Versace]], [[De Beers]], [[Elie Saab]], [[Colcci]], [[Elsa Schiaparelli|Schiaparelli]], [[Prada]], [[Intimissimi]], [[Guess (clothing)|GUESS?]], [[LOEWE (fashion brand)|LOEWE]], [[H&M]], [[Bulgari]], [[Miu Miu]], [[DKNY]], [[Emporio Armani]], [[Givenchy]], [[Keds (shoes)|Keds]], [[Mossimo]], [[Jason Wu]], [[Balmain (fashion house)|Balmain]], [[Blumarine]], [[Marc Jacobs]], [[Maybelline]], [[Max Azria|BCBG]], and [[Louis Vuitton]].\n\nShe also appeared on the covers and in the editorials of other fashion magazines such as ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'', ''[[Elle (magazine)|ELLE]]'', ''[[Grazia]]'', ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'', ''[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]'', ''[[GQ]]'', ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'', ''[[Arena (magazine)|Arena]]'', ''[[V (American magazine)|V]]'', ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]'', ''[[Garage Magazine|Garage]]'', and ''French Revue des Modes''.\n\nHer April 2006 ''GQ'' cover was the highest-selling issue of that magazine for the year.<ref name=\"Forbes models\"/> It was also one of the all-time best selling issues of the publication.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/rankings/ui/TopSexiest/1545#1545|title=MODELS.com's Top Sexiest Models - 5-1|work=Models.com|date=August 12, 2011|accessdate=September 26, 2019}}</ref> The magazine named her \"The World's Most Voluptuous Virgin\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2006/03/16/limas-choice|title=Adriana Lima's new title is \"the world's most voluptuous virgin\"|work=Vogue UK|date=March 16, 2006|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Victoria's Secret models visit Guantanamo, December 2007.jpg|thumb|Victoria's Secret Angels Lima (left), [[Marisa Miller]] and [[Selita Ebanks]] ride in the [[Guantanamo Bay Naval Base|Guantanamo Bay]] Christmas Parade on December 1, 2007 in a [[Cadillac Eldorado]]]]\n\nIn 2006, Lima ranked as the fifth highest paid supermodel. Between 2007 and 2008, she ranked as the world's fourth highest paid supermodel by Forbes Magazine.<ref name=\"Forbes models\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/2007/07/09/models-media-bundchen-biz-media-cz_kb_0716topmodels1_slide.html#7de7ae926a24|title=In Pictures: The World's Top-Earning Models|last=Blakeley|first=Kiri|work=[[Forbes]]|date=July 16, 2007|accessdate=April 8, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"teleuk\">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?xml=/news/2007/07/16/wforbes116.xml |title=Forbes Top Fifteen Models |newspaper=Telegraph|date=July 16, 2007}}</ref><ref name=\"f06\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2006/53/C3P8.html|title=Top 100 Celebrities 2006|work=Forbes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/2008/04/30/models-bundchen-klum-biz-media-cz_kb_0430topmodels_slide_8.html|title=In Pictures: The World's 15 Top-Earning Models|work=[[Forbes]]|date=April 30, 2008|accessdate=December 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, she again fronted the cover of GQ, this time attracting a record number of visits to the publication's website. She also appeared in the 2005 [[Pirelli Calendar]] and became the face of Italy's cell phone carrier, [[Telecom Italia Mobile]], a move that earned her the nickname, \"the [[Catherine Zeta-Jones]] of Italy.\"<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2005/53/C3P8.html |title=Adriana Lima, Forbes Top Celebrities |work=Forbes |accessdate=May 21, 2007}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2008, Lima was featured on the cover of ''Esquire'', re-creating the classic 1966 [[Angie Dickinson]] cover on Esquire's 75th anniversary. She appeared only in shoes, diamonds and gloves for the November 2007 issue of ''Vanity Fair'' celebrating 20 years of supermodels with her fellow Victoria's Secret Angels.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nothing to Hide|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/features/video/2007/victoriassecret_video200711|work=Vanity Fair|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081024061831/http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/features/video/2007/victoriassecret_video200711|archivedate=October 24, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref> In February 2008, she was chosen to be the face of Mexico's [[Liverpool (store)|Liverpool]] department store chain and launched the partnership with a press conference, runway show, and a summer campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wireimage.com/celebrity-pictures/Model-Adriana-Lima-arrives-to-Liverpool-Santa-Fe-to-attend-Fashion/80077473|title=Model Adriana Lima arrives to Liverpool Santa Fe to attend Fashion Fest 2008... 80077473|work=WireImage|date=February 29, 2008|accessdate=November 25, 2012}}</ref>\n\nLima returned to the high fashion runway in 2009, walking for [[Givenchy]]. In the same year, after visiting Turkey, she signed a contract with [[Doritos]] to appear in print campaigns and television commercials which began airing in Turkey that April. She was also one of the faces of Givenchy for the Fall/Winter 2009 season.\n\nIn 2011, Lima signed a deal as a spokeswoman for Megacity by Votsu, a Brazilian social gaming company, to appear in their commercials. Lima has worked with the most established photographers in fashion such as [[Annie Leibovitz]], [[Juergen Teller]], [[Bruce Weber (photographer)|Bruce Weber]], J.R. Duran, [[Paolo Roversi]], [[Inez van Lamsweerde|Inez van Lamsweerde and Vinoodh Matidin]], Vincent Peters, [[Mario Sorrenti]], [[Mert Alas and Marcus Piggott]], [[Steven Meisel]], [[David Sims (photographer)|David Sims]], and [[Mario Testino]].\n\nShe became the face of [[Donna Karan]]'s spring 2012 advertising campaign, which was accused of having racist undertones due to a photo featuring Lima posing in front of huddled local Haitians.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2011/12/15/adriana-lima-donna-karan-ads_n_1152124.html|title=Adriana Lima Donna Karan Ads For Spring 2012: Are They Misguided?|last=Misener|first=Jessica|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=December 15, 2011|accessdate=May 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn early 2012, Turkish clothing company [[Mavi Jeans]], contracted with Lima to be the face and spokesmodel for the brand. In the first quarter of 2012, her advertisement campaign increased sales by 50%. It also provided a 20% increase in stores and online traffic. Furthermore, her television commercial, which was watched by 28 million people, became a trending topic at Twitter and the number of people on Mavi's [[Facebook]] page increased by 20%. Store officials at Mavi say the clothing Lima wore in the ad campaigns was met with so much demand that they ran out of stock. Due to her success rate with the company, the European and Russian branch of Mavi decided to make her the global face of the brand.\n\nLima was photographed by artist Richard Phillips on the famed Copacabana sidewalk in Brazil for Visionaire no. 62 which was released in mid-2012.\n\nIn an interview, Phillips talks about Lima: \"She's so powerful, really an entity, in a way.\" Then added \"You meet her and there's a generosity of spirit and very friendly and easy manner, and then all of sudden, the lights go on, and you realize you're working with this absolutely extraordinary person who's capable of creating these powerful images.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/thecut/2012/09/first-looks-richard-phillips-on-adriana-lima.html |title=First Looks: Artist Richard Phillips Talks Adriana Lima and Lindsay Lohan - The Cut |work=New York Magazine |date=September 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\nFor the second time, she was featured in the Pirelli calendar by setting a record of being the first pregnant woman to be ever featured in the calendar for the 2013 edition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/pirelli-calendar-2013-adriana-lima-pregnant-models-not-nude-first-time-years-photos-905858|title=Pirelli Calendar 2013: Adriana Lima Pregnant, Models Not Nude For The First Time In Years [PHOTOS]|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=November 28, 2012|accessdate=July 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2013, Spanish fashion brand [[Desigual]] announced that Lima would be the face of the brand during Barcelona Fashion Week Spring-Summer '14,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.desigual.com/en/adriana-lima-para-desigual-en-el-080-barcelona-fashion/|title=Desigual blog: Adriana Lima for Desigual in the 080 Barcelona Fashion|publisher=Blog.Desigual.com|accessdate=July 8, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150425210633/http://blog.desigual.com/en/adriana-lima-para-desigual-en-el-080-barcelona-fashion/|archivedate=April 25, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> following [[Bar Refaeli]] in the same role on January 2013. In April 2014, Lima was chosen as the first brand ambassador of Desigual for the brand's 30th anniversary. She has been named the \"ambassador of la vida es Chula\", Desigual's \"life is cool\" motto. Desigual marketing director, Borja Castresana, stated that Adriana \"reflects our values and represents Desigual women who are confident, optimistic and full of life.\" The campaign was launched on 20 April 2014, with television commercials in Spain, France, Germany, Italy, Austria and Belgium.\n\nIn 2013, she ranked as the third highest paid supermodel according to [[Forbes]], with earnings of $6 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/vannale/2013/08/19/the-worlds-highest-paid-models-of-2013/2/|title=The World's Highest Paid Models 2013|last=Le|first=Vanna|work=[[Forbes]]|date=August 19, 2013|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref> In 2014, she ranked as the world's second highest paid supermodel with earnings of $8 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2014/08/18/the-worlds-highest-paid-models-of-2014-gisele-doutzen-and-adriana-steal-the-show/|title=The World's Highest-Paid Models Of 2014: Gisele, Doutzen And Adriana Steal The Show|last=Robehmed|first=Natalie|work=Forbes|date=August 18, 2014|accessdate=August 26, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2014, she returned to her role as a Maybelline New York spokesmodel. She had been the face of the brand between 2003 and 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/adriana-lima-returns-as-maybelline-new-york-spokesmodel|title=Adriana For Maybelline, Again|last=Niven-Phillips|first=Lisa|work=Vogue|date=June 19, 2014|accessdate=November 21, 2019}}</ref> Lima was also chosen as the new face of [[Jason Wu]] Fall/Winter 2014 campaign. Jason Wu stated about Lima, \"She's sexy, and there's this feline-esque prowess that felt appropriate for the clothes. And she's got those eyes! She's like our own [[Bianca Jagger]]. Adriana is a new take on the supermodel - she's from a different era. At the end of the day, these ads are about the women and the sexiness, and I continue to choose women who inspire me.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.ie/style/fashion/fashion-news/adriana-lima-is-the-new-face-of-jason-wu-30383844.html|title=Adriana Lima is the new face of Jason Wu|work=Independent.ie|date=June 25, 2014|accessdate=January 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2014, Lima starred in a campaign for luxury Swiss watch label [[International Watch Company|IWC]] alongside [[Karolina Kurkova]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/adriana-lima-karolina-kurkova-pose-iwc-watches-campaign-peter-lindbergh/|title=Adriana Lima & Karolina Kurkova Pose for IWC Watches Campaign by Peter Lindbergh|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=September 29, 2014|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, she became the face of [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue Eyewear]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popsugar.com/latina/Adriana-Lima-Modeling-Glasses-Vogue-Eyewear-38559458|title=Adriana Lima Modeling Glasses For Vogue Eyewear|work=PopSugar.com|date=October 5, 2015|accessdate=August 20, 2017}}</ref> and of [[Marc Jacobs]]' fragrance ''Decadence''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/designers/news/a10773/adriana-lima-marc-jacobs/|title=Adriana Lima is the Face of Marc Jacobs' New Fragance and His Met Gala Date|last=Kosin|first=Julie|work=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|date=May 4, 2015|accessdate=March 22, 2018}}</ref> In the same year, she was ranked as the world's second highest paid supermodel with earnings of $9 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/fashion/people/forbes-worlds-highest-paid-models-list/|title=Forbes World's Highest Paid Models list, all the latest styles|last=Sowray|first=Bibby|work=[[The Sunday Telegraph]]|date=September 17, 2015|accessdate=July 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2016, Lima became the face of Italian lingerie brand [[Calzedonia]]'s Swimwear collection.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.femalefirst.co.uk/lifestyle-fashion/stylenews/adriana-lima-new-face-calzedonia-937131.html|title=Adriana Lima Is New Face of Calzedonia|publisher=FemaleFirst|date=April 11, 2016|accessdate=January 21, 2017}}</ref> In July 2016, Lima was chosen by [[NBC]] alongside fellow Brazilian model [[Alessandra Ambrosio]] as the channel's food and culture correspondents for the [[2016 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/sports/adriana-lima-and-alessandra-ambrosio-will-be-contributors-at-2016-rio-olympics/|title=Alessandra Ambrosio and Adriana Lima Will Be Olympic Cultural Contributors: 'Sports Run in Our Blood!'|last=Minutaglio|first=Ross|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=July 19, 2016|accessdate=January 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nbcsportsgrouppressbox.com/2016/07/19/brazilian-supermodels-alessandra-ambrosio-and-adriana-lima-join-nbc-olympics-coverage-in-rio/|title=Brazilian supermodels Alessandra Ambrosio and Adriana Lima join NBC Olympics' coverage in Rio|website=NBC Sports Pressbox|date=July 19, 2016|accessdate=January 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, Lima starred in the ready-to-wear Spring/Summer 2017 campaign for the Italian brand [[Sportmax]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/adriana-lima-sportmax-spring-2017-campaign/|title=ADRIANA LIMA TAKES A DIP IN SPORTMAX'S SPRING 2017 ADS|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=January 28, 2017|accessdate=June 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Lima became a brand ambassador for [[Puma (brand)|Puma]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.fashionnetwork.com/news/Adriana-Lima-is-Puma-s-latest-brand-ambassador,1020148.html|title=Adriana Lima is Puma's latest brand ambassador|work=Fashion Network|date=October 2, 2018|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> and for the Brazilian-based footwear and accessories label Schutz.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/adriana-lima-schutz-campaign/|title=Adriana Lima Poses Around NYC in Schutz' Summer 2018 Campaign|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=May 21, 2018|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Lima was the face of Miu Miu cruise campaign,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/kendall-jenner-miu-miu-cruise-2019-campaign/|title=Kendall Jenner Gets Luxe in Miu Miu Cruise 2019 Campaign|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=November 6, 2018|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> of [[Chopard]] Spring/Summer campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/work/chopard-chopard-with-adriana-lima|title=Chopard with Adriana Lima Spring 2019|work=Models.com|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> She was also the face of the Maybelline x Puma collaboration,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/adriana-lima-puma-maybelline-makeup/|title=Adriana Lima PUMA x Maybelline Campaign|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=January 21, 2019|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref> of the Schutz resort 2019 campaign,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashiongonerogue.com/adriana-lima-schutz-resort-19-campaign/|title=Adriana Lima Flaunts Her Legs in Schutz Resort '19 Campaign|work=Fashion Gone Rogue|date=March 15, 2019|accessdate=April 14, 2019}}</ref> and starred in the [[Palms Casino Resort]] commercial with others including [[Cardi B]] and [[Rita Ora]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://us.hola.com/celebrities/2019032822459/cardib-palm-casino-vegas/|title=Mic drop! Watch Cardi B, Ozuna and Adriana Lima's $690 million Las Vegas launch|work=Hola!|date=March 28, 2019|accessdate=April 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Victoria's Secret===\n[[File:Adriana-Lima FantaysBra-Chgo 2010-12-10 photoby-Bielawski.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Adriana Lima with the 2010 Fantasy Bra]]\nLima is probably best known for her work with [[Victoria's Secret]]. She walked her first Victoria's Secret runway in 1999,<ref name=\"People\"/> at age 17<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/adriana-limas-9-favorite-victorias-secret-fashion-show-looks-photos|title=Adriana Lima's 9 Favorite Victoria's Secret Fashion Show Looks (Photos)|last=Cunningham|first=Erin|work=[[The Daily Beast]]|date=December 9, 2013|accessdate=January 31, 2019}}</ref> and since being contracted as an Angel in 2000, she has appeared on subsequent shows ever since, opening the show in 2003, 2007, 2008, and 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/adriana-lima-victorias-secrets-angel-and-her-style-evolution-2001-2011-photos-553452|title=Adriana Lima: Victoria's Secret's Angel and Her Style Evolution from 2001 to 2011 [PHOTOS]|work=International Business Times|date=December 2, 2011|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref> In 2012, she opened the show for the 5th time less than two months after giving birth to her second child.<ref>{{cite wb|url=https://www.today.com/style/adriana-lima-walks-catwalk-two-months-after-giving-birth-flna1C6955809|title= Adriana Lima walks the catwalk \u2014 two months after giving birth|work=Today.com|date=November 8, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2012/11/08/adriana-lima-wows-at-victoria-secret-show-two-months-after-giving-birth/|title=Adriana Lima Wows at Victoria's Secret Show Two Months After Giving Birth|work=Fox News Latino|date=November 8, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121112143222/http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2012/11/08/adriana-lima-wows-at-victoria-secret-show-two-months-after-giving-birth/|archivedate=November 12, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, she was one of the five Angels promoting Victoria's Secret nationwide in the so-called \"Angels Across America\" Tour, alongside [[Tyra Banks]], [[Heidi Klum]], [[Gisele B\u00fcndchen]] and [[Alessandra Ambrosio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zimbio.com/Victoria%27s+Secret+Fashion+Show+2004/articles/b5fCp4A1U_D/Victoria+Secret+Fashion+Show+2004+Angels+Across|title=Victoria's Secret Fashion Show 2004: Angels Across America (Pictures)|work=Zimbio|date=May 20, 2011}}</ref> She missed the 2009 show due to her pregnancy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/adriana-lima-victoria-secret-fashion-192711696.html|title=Adriana Lima's Victoria's Secret Fashion Show Looks Through the Years|work=YaHoo!|date=December 5, 2016}}</ref> Lima has appeared on several television ads for the brand, including the praised and criticized \"Angel in Venice\" commercial of 2003 with [[Bob Dylan]].<ref name=\"usatoday1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/people/2004-04-05-bob-dylan_x.htm|title=Dylan appearing in Victoria's Secret ad|last=Cox|first=Dean|work=[[USA Today]]|date=April 5, 2004|accessdate=September 19, 2007}}</ref>\n\n2008 continued with Lima hosting the ''What Is Sexy?'' program for the E! Entertainment Network and a July tour for the BioFit Uplift Bra launch. She was also featured in November's Miracle Bra relaunch. Topping the year off, Lima wore the \"[[Victoria's Secret Fashion Show#Fantasy Bra|Fantasy Bra]]\" for the 2008 Victoria's Secret Fashion Show. The bra, created by American jewelry designer [[Martin Katz (American jewelry designer)|Martin Katz]], was set with 3,575 black diamonds, 117 certified {{convert|1|carat|mg}} white round diamonds, 34 rubies, and two black diamond drops totaling {{convert|100|carat|g}}. Valued at over $5 million, the bra carried more than {{convert|1500|carat|g}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationaljewelernetwork.com/njn/content_display/fashion/jewelry-fashion-reports/e3i0731a97427122625bd86e624cbcff394|title=Victoria's Secret unveils 2008 'Fantasy Bra|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100114112343/http://www.nationaljewelernetwork.com/njn/content_display/fashion/jewelry-fashion-reports/e3i0731a97427122625bd86e624cbcff394|archivedate=January 14, 2010|work=[[Jewelers of America#National Jeweler|National Jeweler]]|date=October 20, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, she again wore the Fantasy Bra, called the Victoria's Secret Bombshell Fantasy Bra. The bra which weighs in at 142 carats with 60 carats of white diamonds and 82 carats of topazes and sapphires is worth 2 million dollars.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2010/10/20/exclusive-adriana-lima-in-2-million-dollar-victorias-secret-bombshell-fantasy-bra/|title=EXCLUSIVE: Watch Adriana Lima Show Off Victoria's Secret $2 Million Bra|work=People|date=February 10, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314175906/http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2010/10/20/exclusive-adriana-lima-in-2-million-dollar-victorias-secret-bombshell-fantasy-bra/|archivedate=March 14, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> She wore the fantasy bra again in 2014, along with Alessandra Ambrosio, with each bra valuing $2,000,000.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://people.com/style/victorias-secret-fantasy-bras-yep-there-are-two-for-2014-get-the-first-look-and-exclusive-photos/ |title=Victoria's Secret Fantasy Bras (Yep, There are Two!) for 2014: Get the First Look and Exclusive Photos! |date=November 1, 2014 |website=People}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2016, Victoria's Secret launched its own sports bra line, ''Victoria Sport'', and Lima starred on the commercial alongside models [[Elsa Hosk]], [[Romee Strijd]], [[Jasmine Tookes]] and [[Josephine Skriver]].<ref>{{YouTube|-1jTNlOPG6Q|Introducing Victoria Sport}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/victorias-secret-sport-photoshoot/|title=Adriana Lima & More Angels Work Up a Sweat in Victoria Sport|work=Fashion Rogue|date=November 6, 2016|accessdate=May 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, Lima was named \"the most valuable Victoria's Secret Angel\" according to analytics company D'Marie,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whowhatwear.com/most-valuable-victorias-secret-model/slide5|title=This Is Officially the Most Valuable Victoria's Secret Angel|work=Who What Wear|date=January 2, 2017|accessdate=January 17, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118053351/http://www.whowhatwear.com/most-valuable-victorias-secret-model/slide5|archivedate=January 18, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> which conducted research that factored in social media likes, followers, sales conversions and engagement to come up with the results. \"We've developed an algorithm that compiles over 24 specific metrics from each social media platform that determines an individual's ranking amongst others' in any variety of categories,\" D'Marie explained.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/life-style/fashion/88173889/adriana-lima-named-most-valuable-victorias-secret-angel|title=Adriana Lima named most valuable Victoria's Secret Angel|work=[[Stuff.co.nz]]|date=January 6, 2017|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2018, Lima walked in her final Victoria's Secret Fashion Show after participating in 20 catwalks for the brand.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/adriana-lima-final-victorias-secret-fashion-show-2018|title=See Adriana Lima's Emotional Final Walk for Victoria's Secret|last=Okwodu|first=Janelle|work=Vogue|date=November 8, 2018|accessdate=November 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Acting and hosting===\nLima's made her acting debut alongside [[Mickey Rourke]] and [[Forest Whitaker]], in ''[[The Hire#The Follow|The Follow]]'' (2001), a short film in [[BMW]]'s series ''[[The Hire]]'', opposite [[Clive Owen]] and directed by [[Wong Kar-wai]]. She also appeared with her fellow Angels in a guest spot playing herself in the [[CBS]] comedy series ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]'' in November 2007, in the episode \"[[The Yips (How I Met Your Mother)|The Yips]]\". She also played herself, along with fellow Victoria's Secret Angels, in the 2013 series ''[[The Crazy Ones]]'' alongside [[Robin Williams]] and [[Sarah Michelle Gellar]]. In 2008, Lima appeared on the American television series ''[[Ugly Betty]]'', where she played herself and made friends with the series' title character, [[Betty Suarez]].\n\nLima was the host and executive producer of the American reality competition show ''American Beauty Stars'', which premiered on September 23, 2017 on [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2017/09/20/supermodel-adriana-lima-takes-us-set-lifetimes-american-beauty-star/664689001/|title=Supermodel Adriana Lima takes us on the set of Lifetime's 'American Beauty Star'|last=Mallenbaum|first=Carly|work=[[USA Today]]|date=September 20, 2017|accessdate=September 24, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Lima made a cameo appearance as herself in the film ''[[Ocean's 8]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/oceans-8-cameos-saul-yen-matt-damon/2/ |title=Ocean's 8: ALL of the Cameos You Missed |date=June 9, 2018 |website=Screen Rant}}</ref>\n\n===Super Bowl ads===\nLima's 2008 solo Victoria's Secret's [[Super Bowl XLII]] ad was the single most-seen ad of the game, watched by 103.7 million viewers.<ref name=\"usatoday2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/money/advertising/2008-02-07-super-bowl-ads_N.htm |title=Close Super Bowl puts even more eyes on late-airing ads|work=USA Today|date=July 2, 2008}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2012, Lima became the only celebrity to ever star in two Super Bowl commercials in one game. She starred in [[Super Bowl XLVI]] commercials for online flower service [[Teleflora]] and [[Kia Motors]] which were watched by more than 200 million viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/entertainmentnewsbuzz/2012/02/super-bowl-ads-teleflora-taps-model-adriana-lima.html|title=Super Bowl ads: Super model Adriana Lima in demand |work=Los Angeles Times|date=February 3, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/fash-track/adriana-lima-super-bowl-commercials-gisele-bundchen-287276|title=Model Adriana Lima Stars in Two Super Hot Super Bowl Commercials|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 6, 2012}}</ref> Her Kia Motors Super Bowl commercial \u2013 promoting the new Kia Optima \u2013 sent sales to their highest mark since the design debuted. Sales were up 31% from January 2012 and 138.6% from February 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/kicking-tires/post/did-super-bowl-xlvi-ads-impact-car-sales/2012/03/02/gIQAtUllmR_blog.html|title=Did Super Bowl XLVI Ads Impact Car Sales|author=Cars.com|work=The Washington Post|date=March 2, 2012|accessdate=July 7, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.suntimes.com/news/steinberg/13178798-452/obama-needs-a-brazilian-supermodel.html|title=Obama needs a Brazilian supermodel|work=Chicago Sun-Times|accessdate=July 7, 2012}}</ref> The commercial was also voted No.3 out of the 55 commercials on USA TODAY and Facebook's Super Bowl Ad Meter.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/superbowl46/admeter.htm |title=2012 USA TODAY Facebook Super Bowl Ad Meter: Rate the ads |work=USA Today |date=February 5, 2012 |accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/money/advertising/story/2012-02-07/usa-today-facebook-super-bowl-ad-meter-final-scores/53004026/1|title=USA TODAY Facebook Super Bowl Ad Meter Scores|date=February 8, 2012|work=USA Today|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120415220228/https://www.usatoday.com/money/advertising/story/2012-02-07/usa-today-facebook-super-bowl-ad-meter-final-scores/53004026/1|archivedate=April 15, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> A teaser of the commercial was released in movie theaters in January before the game. It is believed to be the first time a Super Bowl commercial premiered in movie theaters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/entertainmentnewsbuzz/2012/01/kia-motors-usa-to-premiere-super-bowl-ad-in-theaters.html|title=Kia Motors USA to premiere Super Bowl ad in theaters|work=Los Angeles Times|date=January 20, 2012|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref>\n\nForbes named her Teleflora commercial as one of the best during Super Bowl XLVI, with the comment, \"Teleflora ... Adriana Lima. 'Nuff said\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/prishe/2012/02/06/the-winners-and-losers-of-super-bowl-commercials-in-2012/|title=The Winners and Losers of Super Bowl Commercials in 2012|last=Rishe|first=Patrick|work=Forbes|date=April 18, 2012|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref> Among the many reviews of the commercial, The Huffington Post said: \"One of the basic goals of any commercial is to capture the viewer's attention, and by this measure, Teleflora.com's ad featuring supermodel Adriana Lima was most definitely successful.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/02/06/super-bowl-commercials-2012-adriana-lima-video_n_1255185.html|title=Adriana Lima Teleflora.Com Super Bowl Commercial: Sexy Ad Stirs Controversy (VIDEO)|last=Greenberg|first=Chris|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=February 6, 2012|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref> ESPN.com noted: \"This actually makes sense when you think about it: Launch your Valentine's Day campaign in the middle of the Super Bowl. That's actually what flower company Teleflora is doing on Sunday. Even smarter? Hire supermodel Adriana Lima to star in it.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/espn/page2/story/_/id/7527035/from-bark-side-bueller-look-2012-super-bowl-commercials|title=Many Super Bowl commercials are out|last=Carter|first=Kelley|work=[[ESPN]]|date=February 1, 2012|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nFrom 2001 to 2003, Lima was in a relationship with American singer [[Lenny Kravitz]].<ref name=\"ISTO\u00c9\"/> They moved in together and got engaged.<ref name=\"ISTO\u00c9\"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/lenny-kravitz-the-star-is-born-again-231577/ |title=Lenny Kravitz: The Star Is Born Again |last=Edwards |first=Gavin |date=June 24, 2004 |website=Rolling Stone}}</ref> Lima was featured on the music video for Kravitz's 2002 single, \"[[Lenny (album)|Yesterday Is Gone (My Dear Kay)]]\".<ref name=\"yesterday\">{{YouTube|id=1zGJZSvuBfI|title=Lenny Kravitz - Yesterday Is Gone (My Dear Kay)}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, Lima married Serbian [[National Basketball Association|NBA]] player [[Marko Jari\u0107]] on [[Valentine's Day]] in [[Jackson Hole, Wyoming]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2009/02/adriana_lima_got_married.html|title=Adriana Lima Got Married|last=Odell|first=Amy|work=[[New York Magazine]]|date=February 24, 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"people1\">{{cite web|last=Wihlborg|first=Ulrica |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20261007,00.html|title=Supermodel Adriana Lima Elopes!|work=People|date=February 23, 2009}}</ref> In May 2009, it was reported that Lima had applied for Serbian citizenship,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rts.rs/page/stories/sr/story/15/Zanimljivosti/64169/Ne+srpska+snajka%2C+ve%C4%87+snajka+Srpkinja.html |title=Adrijana Lima \u017eeli dr\u017eavljanstvo Srbije|work=Radio-televizjia Srbije|language=Serbian|date=May 27, 2009}}</ref> but it was never granted to her.<ref name=\"Alo-not-citizen\">{{cite web|url=http://www.alo.rs/v-i-p/svetski-dzet-set/adrijana-lima-nikada-nije-uzela-srpski-pasos/54368|title=Adrijana Lima nikada nije uzela srpski paso\u0161!|trans-title=Adriana Lima Never Took Serbian Passport!|publisher=[[Alo (newspaper)|Alo]]|date=May 8, 2014|accessdate=April 1, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701163330/http://www.alo.rs/v-i-p/svetski-dzet-set/adrijana-lima-nikada-nije-uzela-srpski-pasos/54368|archivedate=July 1, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Jari\u0107 and Lima have two daughters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-moms/news/adriana-lima-gives-birth-to-daughter-sienna-2012129/|title=Adriana Lima Gives Birth to Daughter Sienna! |work=UsMagazine.com|date=September 12, 2012}}</ref> On May 2, 2014, Lima and Jari\u0107 announced their separation after five years of marriage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/adriana-lima-husband-marko-jaric-split-supermodel-announces-divorce-201425/|title=Adriana Lima Splits From Husband Marko Jaric After 5 Years of Marriage: Supermodel Announces Separation From Former NBA Player|last=Lee|first=Esther|work=[[Us Weekly]]|date=May 2, 2014|accessdate=August 13, 2018}}</ref> The divorce was finalized in March 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pagesix.com/2016/03/15/adriana-lima-and-marko-jaric-finalize-divorce/|title=Adriana Lima is divorced|last=Johnson|first=Richard|work=Page Six|date=March 15, 2015|accessdate=September 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Religious views===\nLima is a devout Roman Catholic who attends [[Mass (Catholic Church)|Mass]] every Sunday. In April 2006, she told ''GQ'' that she was a [[Virginity|virgin]]. \"Sex is for after marriage,\" she said. \"[Men] have to respect that this is my choice. If there's no respect, that means they don't want me.\" She also denounced [[abortion]] as a crime, and stated that she agrees with all of the Church's teachings.<ref name=gq>{{cite magazine|first=Lisa|last=DePaulo|url=https://www.gq.com/women/photos/200603/adriana-lima-virgin-underwear-model|title=Adriana Lima: Our favorite ... virgin?|magazine=[[GQ]]|location=New York City|date=April 2006}}</ref><ref name=\"plan\">{{cite web|url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0506/17/sbt.01.html|title=Tom Cruise Proposes to Katie Holmes; Angelina Jolie's Personal Life Full of Drama; Picks and Pans of New Movies|work=[[Showbiz Tonight]]|date=June 17, 2005}}</ref> Lima is known to bring a [[Bible]] with her backstage before she goes onstage. She has also stated that, before she became a [[Victoria's Secret Angel]], she had wanted to become a [[nun]]. Regarding her spirituality, Lima stated, \"The church is in me \u2014 I always connect. If you're connected with the divine and always have pure intentions with everything you're doing, you're protected by the angels. I'm very spiritual. I believe in nature, I believe in energy, I believe in spirits.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/victorias-secret-angel-adriana-lima-the-church-is-in-me|title=Adriana Lima wanted to be a nun|work=[[Fox News]]|date=February 27, 2017|accessdate=August 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Charity work===\nLima does charitable work helping with an [[orphanage]], \"Caminhos da Luz\" (Paths of Light), located in Salvador. She helps with construction to expand the orphanage and buys clothes for poor children in Salvador, Bahia.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pirelli.com/tyre/br/pt/news/2012/10/01/calendario-pirelli-2013-por-steve-mccurry/ |title=Calend\u00e1rio Pirelli 2013 por Steve McCurry |date=October 1, 2012 |website=Pirelli.com |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref name=\"caminhosdaluz\">[https://archive.today/20130104205852/http://www.superiorpics.com/adriana_lima/interview.html Adriana helping her charity]. Superiorpics.com. Retrieved 2011-08-10.</ref> In 2009, she appeared on ''[[Var m\u0131s\u0131n? Yok musun?]]'', the Turkish version of ''[[Deal or No Deal]]'', where her prize money went to a hospital in [[Istanbul]] for children fighting leukemia.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/cadde/galeri/var-misin-yok-musunda-adriana-ruzgari-1051661/1 |title=Var m\u0131s\u0131n yok musun'da Adriana r\u00fczgar\u0131 |date=January 26, 2009 |website=milliyet.com |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IqsGi1a0VT8 |title=BESIKTAS'LI ADRIANA LIMA WINS 75,000$ on Deal or No Deal |date=January 26, 2009 |website=YouTube}}</ref>\n\n==Public image==\nLima was listed in the 2005 Forbes' edition of The World's Best-Paid Celebrities Under 25.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://moneycentral.msn.com/content/invest/forbes/P140854.asp|title=Forbes: The World's Best-Paid Celebrities Under 25 |work=MSN |date=January 11, 2006|accessdate=October 10, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090125213125/http://moneycentral.msn.com/content/invest/forbes/P140854.asp|archive-date=January 25, 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref> She ranked ninety-nine in the 2005 and 2006 Forbes' edition of The [[Celebrity 100]] lists.<ref>{{cite web|author=Lea Goldman & Kiri Blakely|url=https://www.forbes.com/2006/06/12/06celebrities_money-power-celebrities-list_land.html|title=The Celebrity 100 |work=Forbes|date=June 15, 2006}}</ref> In 2012, she was listed in Forbes Celebrity 100 power list for earning more than 7 million between May 2011 and May 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hannahelliott/2012/05/16/on-the-celebrity-100-gisele-tops-kate/|title=On The Celebrity 100, Gisele Tops Kate|first=Hannah|last=Elliott|publisher=|accessdate=July 28, 2016}}</ref> In 2012, she ranked number eight in forbes' \"The World's Most Powerful Latino Celebrities\" list for earning more than 7 million dollars.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2012/05/25/the-worlds-most-powerful-latino-celebrities/2/ |title=The World's Most Powerful Latino Celebraties|work=Forbes|date=May 25, 2012}}</ref>\n\nLima was chosen to be a part of ''People'' magazine's 100 most beautiful people in the world list, sharing that space with the Angels, with whom she also received a star on the Hollywood \"Walk of Fame\" prior to the 2007 Victoria's Secret Fashion Show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.starpulse.com/Supermodels/Lima,_Adriana/Videos/?vxChannel=&vxClipId=&clip_id=9juVYym30l9QrCE1&video_title=USA%3A+Victoria's+Secret%22angels%22honored+with+a+star+on+the+Hollywood+walk+of+fame |title=USA: Victoria's Secret\"angels\"honored with a star on the Hollywood walk of fame Video - Adriana Lima Videos |publisher=Starpulse.com |accessdate=2012-10-25}}</ref> That same year, she ranked 7th on ''[[FHM]]''s \"[[FHM's 100 Sexiest Women (UK)|100 Sexiest Women 2007]]\" list.<ref name=\"fhm\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fhmonline.com/girls_100_sexiest_2007.asp?cnl_id=1&stn_id=136&p=48|title=No.7 Adriana Lima and No.6 Jessica Biel \u2013 100 Sexiest Women 2007|work=[[FHM]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070606103259/http://www.fhmonline.com/girls_100_sexiest_2007.asp?cnl_id=1&stn_id=136&p=48 |archivedate=June 6, 2007}}</ref>\n\nLima was also voted on ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]''{{'}}s \"Hot 100\" 2007 at the No. 53 spot. She was voted No.1 as the Most Desirable Woman in 2005 by visitors of the men's lifestyle website [[AskMen]].com and placed 4th in 2006 and 2007, 10th in 2008, and 19th in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ca.askmen.com/media_kit/press_release/press_release_a14.html |title=AskMen.com - Press Releases |publisher=AskMen |date=January 31, 2008 |accessdate=October 25, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113113237/http://ca.askmen.com/media_kit/press_release/press_release_a14.html |archivedate=November 13, 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.askmen.com/media_kit/press_release/press_release_a11.html |title=Press Releases |publisher=AskMen.com |accessdate=October 25, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113113237/http://www.askmen.com/media_kit/press_release/press_release_a11.html |archivedate=November 13, 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref> She received the award for \"Hottest Girl on the Planet\" in the 2007 [[Spike Guys' Choice Awards]].<ref>[[Spike Guys' Choice Awards]]</ref> Since November 2008, Models.com has featured her at number one on the list of the \"Sexiest Models\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/rankings/sexiest/list.html?model_id=1545#1545|title=No.1 Sexiest model|work= Models.com|accessdate=October 8, 2011}}</ref> In July 2011, she was ranked No. 4 in the website's \"Money Girls\" list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/rankings/money/list.html?model_id=1545#1545 |title=Money Girls List|work=Models.com}}</ref> The website also lists her on \"the Supers\" list. The list, which has only 8 [[supermodels]], is about supermodels that transcend the boundaries of the fashion industry and have public recognition in and out of fashion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://models.com/rankings/ui/TheSupers|title=MODELS.com's The Supers|work=Models.com}}</ref> In 2010, she was voted eighth in \"[[FHM's 100 Sexiest Women (UK)|FHM's Sexiest Women in the World]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/100-sexiest-2009/adriana-lima/|title=FHM Ranking - 100 Sexiest of 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090715231033/http://www.fhm.com/100-sexiest-2009/adriana-lima/|work=FHM.com|archivedate=July 15, 2009|url-status=dead}}</ref> FHM ranked her at No. 6 in 2009, No. 21 in 2008 and No. 4 in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/adriana-lima|title=Adriana Lima|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110109195042/http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/adriana-lima|archivedate=January 9, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, Lima was ranked No. 46 on the 50 most popular women on the Web according to Google search results.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Technology/50-popular-women-web-google-search-results/story?id=10573331|title=50 Most Popular Women on the Web, Per Google Search Results|work=ABC News|date=May 6, 2010}} April 15, 2010, COED Magavine.</ref> A results from a market research study in 2011 about the [[UEFA Champions League]] released by [[Heineken]], showed that 52% of men would rather watch their team lift the Champions League trophy than go on a date with Lima.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2011/05/23/1670831/0/en/Men-Give-Up-Supermodels-for-Champions-League-Final.html |title=Men Give Up Supermodels for Champions League Final |date=May 23, 2011 |website=GlobeNewsWire}}</ref> [[McAfee]] ranked Lima as the 6th most \"dangerous\" celebrity in cyberspace in 2010. The ranking, relating to the use of the names of popular celebrities to lure people to websites that are laden with [[malicious software]], ranked Lima number eight in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://home.mcafee.com/advicecenter/most-dangerous-celebrities?ctst=1|title=Heidi Klum Named Most Dangerous Celebrity in Cyberspace|work=mcafee.com|date=September 15, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111217121808/http://home.mcafee.com/advicecenter/most-dangerous-celebrities?ctst=1|archivedate=December 17, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2012, [[Complex (magazine)|Complex]] ranked her 4th in the list of \"The 100 Hottest Supermodels of All Time\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2012/11/the-100-hottest-supermodels-of-all-time/#gallery|title=The 100 Hottest Supermodels of All Time|work=Complex|date=November 15, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn October 6, 2015, it was announced that Adriana will have her own wax figure at the [[Madame Tussauds New York]]. She is the first Victoria's Secret Angel and the second Brazilian figure to join the Tussauds star lineup, after soccer star [[Pel\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Wax figure of Adriana Lima added to Madame Tussauds New York|url=https://news.yahoo.com/wax-figure-adriana-lima-added-madame-tussauds-york-124207430.html|publisher=[[Yahoo]]|date=October 6, 2015}}</ref> Her wax figure was unveiled on 30 November 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/adriana-lima-madame-tussauds-wax-figure|title=Adriana Lima Is the Most Famous Victoria's Secret Angel|last=Okwodu|first=Janelle|work=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|date=November 30, 2015|accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, she was chosen as the Fashion Icon honoree at the Daily Front Row Awards.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://sg.style.yahoo.com/adriana-lima-honoured-daily-front-row-fashion-awards-010000314.html |title=Adriana Lima honoured at Daily Front Row Fashion Awards |date=March 17, 2019 |website=Yahoo!}}</ref>\n\n===Criticism===\nIn a 2011 interview with ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'', prior to the Victoria's Secret Fashion Show, Lima said that for nine days before the show she drinks only [[protein shake]]s, and no liquids at all for the last 12 hours \"so you dry out, sometimes you can lose up to eight pounds just from that.\" She also stated that for the last three weeks before the show, she works out twice a day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/news-features/TMG8872623/Victorias-Secret-show-What-does-it-take-to-be-a-Victorias-Secret-Angel.html|title=Victoria's Secret show: What does it take to be a Victoria's Secret Angel?|last=Whitworth|first=Melissa|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=November 7, 2011|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref> The interview prompted criticism from the media commentators.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.styleite.com/media/anderson-cooper-adriana-lima-ridiculist/|title=Anderson Cooper &#124; Adriana Lima's Diet &#124; The Ridiculist|last=Fenner|first=Justin|work=Styleite|date=November 11, 2011|accessdate=December 25, 2012}}</ref> Shortly afterwards, Lima defended herself in an interview with [[E!]]. \"I know it's very intense but ... I just have an athlete's mind and I appreciate doing this thing,\" she said. \"It's not that I do crazy diets throughout the year. I just do it for this particular thing. After this show, I become normal again.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/bodies/victorias-secret-fashion-show-adriana-lima-extreme-diet/|title=Victoria's Secret Fashion Show: Adriana Lima Extreme Diet|last=Hammel|first=Sara|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=November 11, 2011|accessdate=March 31, 2019}}</ref> The Adriana Lima diet became one of the top five most searched diets on the web in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://healthland.time.com/2012/12/12/the-most-popular-diets-of-2012-according-to-google/slide/adriana-lima-diet/|title=The Most Popular Diets Of 2012 (According To Google)|last=Sifferlin|first=Alexandra|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=December 12, 2012|accessdate=November 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''Pista Dupla''\n|\n| TV series\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[The Hire: The Follow]]''\n| The Wife\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"The Yips\"\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Ugly Betty]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Ugly Betty\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[The Crazy Ones]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Models Love Magic\"\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Ocean's 8]]''\n| Herself\n| Cameo\n|-\n|}\n\n==Music video==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Artist\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Yesterday Is Gone (My Dear Kay)]]''\n| [[Lenny Kravitz]]<ref name=\"yesterday\"/>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Adriana Lima}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb name|0992596|Adriana Lima}}\n* {{Models.com}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20151229222616/http://www.thefashionstyles.com/adriana-lima/ Adriana Lima] at Fashion Styles\n* [http://www.vogue.com/tag/model/adriana-lima Adriana Lima] at [[Vogue Magazine]]\n* {{Fashionmodel}}\n\n{{Victoria'